{"type":"message","id":"53fd3083","parentId":"22038749","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:05:00.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `NODE_PATH` only works for CommonJS `require()`, not for ESM `import`. The scripts use ES modules (they have `import` statements). For ESM, I need to use `--experimental-require-module` or the import map `--import`.\n\nActually, for Node.js 24, ESM module resolution doesn't respect `NODE_PATH`. I need a different approach:\n\n1. Install playwright locally in the plugin-skills directory or workspace\n2. Or use `--experimental-specifier-resolution=node` \n3. Or just install playwright in the workspace\n\nActually, let me try a simpler approach - install playwright as a local dependency.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_JkWSN5WW7F0sfK57abft9843","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 在 workspace 下装 playwright 以便 ESM 能解析\ncd \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\"\nnpm init -y --silent 2>$null\nnpm install playwright 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":605,"output":254,"cacheRead":80768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81627,"cost":{"input":0.00008470000000000001,"output":0.00007112000000000001,"cacheRead":0.002261504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002417324}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781492697184,"responseId":"38e0dafc-8d72-46df-822a-ebc2d80753bd"}}
