{"type":"message","id":"57385ec7","parentId":"269b3462","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:08:26.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Cursor CLI doesn't seem to have a clear \"send message to agent\" API. But it does have `--add-mcp` which can add MCP servers. And there's `cursor agent` subcommand.\n\nLet me try `cursor agent` with PTY to see what it does interactively. But actually, let me look at what `cursor --add-mcp` can do - this is promising. I could set up an MCP server that lets Cursor talk to OpenClaw or vice versa.\n\nActually, the most practical approach might be:\n\n1. **`cursor agent`** — This starts the Cursor AI agent in terminal (like Claude Code). I can pipe instructions to it.\n2. **`cursor --add-mcp`** — Register an MCP server so Cursor can use OpenClaw's tools.\n3. **`cursor -g <file:line>`** — Open files in Cursor (navigation only).\n4. **`cursor --goto <file> <<< \"instruction\"`** — Open with stdin.\n\nLet me test `cursor agent` more concretely.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9BiGQitxKdAVRPedUt1l8840","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试用 pipe 向 cursor agent 发指令\necho '帮我检查一下当前工作区有没有 package.json' | cursor agent --yes 2>&1","timeout":30,"pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1532,"output":337,"cacheRead":111232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113101,"cost":{"input":0.00021448000000000002,"output":0.00009436000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003114496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003423336}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781503701028,"responseId":"ee026267-9172-4c3a-9484-453888f34e69"}}
