{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6dcdc0d8f8a4b4cfdfe36fc0574\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"sender\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-06-15 14:17 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Yousan(叶枝君) (ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"name\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"87a4e867","parentId":"97fdea62","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:17:09.790Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"a7d85e72","parentId":"87a4e867","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:17:19.546Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to send messages from their phone (via Feishu/飞书) to me (OpenClaw), and have me relay those instructions to Cursor to execute project tasks.\n\nSo the flow would be:\n1. User sends message on phone (Feishu) → OpenClaw\n2. OpenClaw receives the message and relays it to Cursor\n3. Cursor executes the task in the project\n\nThe best approach for this is to set up an MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration where I can send instructions to Cursor. Let me think about what's possible:\n\n1. **`cursor agent` via PTY** - I could spawn a `cursor agent` session in the background and send instructions to it. But this is a terminal-based interactive session.\n\n2. **`cursor --add-mcp`** - Register OpenClaw as an MCP server for Cursor. This makes Cursor able to call my tools, but doesn't help me send instructions TO Cursor.\n\n3. **File-based approach** - I create/modify files in the project, and Cursor detects changes. But this doesn't execute tasks, just presents changes.\n\n4. **Write task files** - I write `.cursor/tasks/xxx.md` or similar that Cursor's agent picks up.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The `cursor agent` subcommand starts a terminal agent. I could:\n- Start `cursor agent` as a background process with PTY\n- Send instructions to it via PTY stdin\n- Read responses\n\nLet me test if `cursor agent` can work non-interactively by piping input.\n\nActually, the most robust approach would be to set up a bidirectional bridge. Let me think about what's the simplest working solution:\n\n1. **`cursor --add-mcp`** approach: Register an MCP server that Cursor can call. But this is Cursor → OpenClaw, not OpenClaw → Cursor.\n\n2. **PTY bridge to `cursor agent`**: I spawn `cursor agent` in PTY mode, and I can send/receive messages. This would work but needs a persistent session.\n\n3. **Batch script approach**: Write a task description to a file, then use `cursor -g` to open it, then somehow trigger the agent. But there's no CLI flag to trigger agent execution.\n\nLet me test option 2 - can I pipe instructions to `cursor agent`?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"理解了，目标是这个链路：**手机飞书 → 我(OpenClaw) → Cursor → 执行项目任务**\n\n最合适的方案是通过 `cursor agent` 的终端模式做桥接。让我先验证一下可行性："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_TzFA6n0rr2FOdIo9ZRGr3015","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 测试 cursor agent 是否能通过 pipe 接收指令\n$msg = '请告诉我你当前的工作目录和项目信息'\n$msg | cursor agent 2>&1 &\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 5\n# 检查有没有启动\nGet-Process -Name \"cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, ProcessName","timeout":20,"pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":8328,"output":704,"cacheRead":105728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114760,"cost":{"input":0.00116592,"output":0.00019712,"cacheRead":0.002960384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004323424}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504229790,"responseId":"cda452fb-185c-476c-9f2c-9beb72482be5"}}
