{"type":"message","id":"da5dcec2","parentId":"cd9c9f96","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:17:27.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The PowerShell background operator `&` doesn't work in this context. Let me try a different approach - start `cursor agent` in a separate process and interact with it. \n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The `cursor agent` command starts an interactive terminal session. I can:\n\n1. Use `sessions_spawn` to create a sub-agent that runs `cursor agent` in PTY mode\n2. Then send messages to it\n\nBut this is complex. Let me think about simpler approaches.\n\nActually, Cursor has a `.cursor/rules/` or `.cursor/tasks/` mechanism. Let me check:\n- `.cursorrules` - project-level instructions for Cursor\n- `.cursor/tasks/` - task files that Cursor agent picks up\n\nAnother approach: I can write to a tasks file in the project directory, and when the user opens Cursor, the agent will pick up the task.\n\nBut the user wants Cursor to EXECUTE tasks automatically in the background, not just have them queued.\n\nLet me look at what `cursor agent` does more carefully, and also look at the Cursor settings for MCP.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2TBAFxFyzzG6SFUWlJdB1269","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看 cursor 的 MCP 配置\nGet-Content \"$env:APPDATA\\Cursor\\User\\globalStorage\\rooveterinaryinc.roo-cline\\mcp_settings.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nGet-Content \"$env:APPDATA\\Cursor\\User\\globalStorage\\continue.continue\\config.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 20\n\n# 看看 .cursor 目录结构\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\**\\.cursor\" -Directory -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\n# 找项目目录\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\projects\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 5\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\source\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 5\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\code\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 5\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\Desktop\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 10","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":239,"output":569,"cacheRead":114688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115496,"cost":{"input":0.00003346,"output":0.00015932,"cacheRead":0.003211264,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003404044}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504240909,"responseId":"bd124595-0f6a-419e-8080-2d54f4683995"}}
