{"type":"message","id":"d9f8f3fa","parentId":"64224569","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:06.539Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cursor agent seems to have started but there's no visible output. It might be waiting for more input or it's running interactively. Let me try a different approach - use `cursor agent` as a subprocess that I can interact with via PTY.\n\nActually, let me take a step back and think about the simplest practical approach that works TODAY.\n\nLooking at what I know:\n1. `cursor agent` starts a terminal agent - it's an interactive session\n2. There's no `cursor exec \"instruction\"` CLI\n3. Cursor watches files in the project\n\nThe most practical approach might be:\n\n**Write a \"Cursor Agent Bridge\" script** that:\n1. Takes a task instruction from me\n2. Writes it to a file in the project\n3. Triggers `cursor agent` via PTY\n\nBut actually, the simplest approach for the user's use case (phone → Feishu → me → Cursor) is:\n\n1. I write the task to a file in their project workspace (e.g., `~/project/.cursor/tasks/pending_task.md`)\n2. Use `cursor -g` to open it in Cursor\n3. The user sees it when they're at their computer\n\nBut the user wants Cursor to EXECUTE the task, not just see it. This is harder.\n\nLet me think about the MCP approach. The `--add-mcp` flag can register an MCP server. If I register OpenClaw as an MCP server for Cursor, then Cursor's agent can call my tools. But the user wants me to be the initiator, not Cursor.\n\nOK, let me think about this differently. The most practical approaches:\n\n**Approach 1: Agent bridge via `cursor agent` PTY**\n- I spawn `cursor agent` in a subagent, connected via PTY\n- I send instructions through the PTY\n- The agent processes them\n\n**Approach 2: MCP server - reverse direction**\n- I create an MCP server that listens for instructions\n- Cursor is configured to poll this MCP server\n- When I write a task to the MCP server, Cursor picks it up\n\n**Approach 3: Write file + trigger Cursor**\n- I write task instructions to a project file\n- Use some mechanism to trigger Cursor's agent\n\nActually, I just realized something. The `cursor agent` command starts a terminal agent. When I pipe input to it, it should read from stdin. Let me try a different approach - use `sessions_spawn` to create a sub-agent that runs `cursor agent` in PTY mode, then I can send messages to the sub-agent.\n\nBut actually, let me first just try to make cursor agent work with piped input in a simpler way.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9TQFYIPo7rQSL7qJ6r2k0342","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try passing instruction as a direct argument through stdin\n$env:CURSOR_AGENT_NO_GUI = \"1\"; echo \"list files in current directory\" | cursor agent 2>&1","timeout":30,"pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":97,"output":700,"cacheRead":129536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130333,"cost":{"input":0.00001358,"output":0.00019600000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0036270079999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0038365879999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504277453,"responseId":"9e7d1c1c-11a7-4764-972d-5dc8c09d05c0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f41a8a4b","parentId":"d9f8f3fa","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:08.273Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_9TQFYIPo7rQSL7qJ6r2k0342","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1722,"aggregated":"[?25l[2J[m[H]0;C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504288273}}
{"type":"message","id":"85c2b27e","parentId":"f41a8a4b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:14.142Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cursor agent starts but seems to immediately exit without output. This might be because:\n1. It's running in a non-TTY environment and doesn't accept piped input\n2. It's designed for interactive terminal use only\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to directly interact with cursor agent via pipe, I can:\n\n1. **Approach: Write a persistent bridge script**\n   - Create a Node.js script that spawns `cursor agent` as a child process with a PTY\n   - It listens on a local HTTP server for incoming tasks\n   - I call the HTTP endpoint to submit tasks\n   - The script pipes the task to cursor agent\n\nLet me think about this differently. Actually, let me look at how the Cursor agent is started and if there's a way to pass an initial prompt.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XBmepLoJhyy8RZJLxPWZ8448","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 cursor agent 的行为 - 也许需要工作目录\n# 先 cd 到项目目录再试\n$projDir = \"E:\\Solo-nightoffullmoon\"\nif (Test-Path $projDir) {\n    cd $projDir\n    \"列出当前目录的文件\" | cursor agent --working-dir $projDir 2>&1\n} else {\n    Write-Output \"Project dir not found, checking others...\"\n    Get-ChildItem \"E:\\\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 10\n    Get-ChildItem \"D:\\\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 10\n}","timeout":30,"pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":74,"output":397,"cacheRead":130304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130775,"cost":{"input":0.00001036,"output":0.00011116000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003648512,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003770032}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504288275,"responseId":"4c386564-5675-474f-96d4-d48698909e80"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e05b967","parentId":"85c2b27e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:15.424Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_XBmepLoJhyy8RZJLxPWZ8448","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[?25l[2J[m[HProject dir not found, checking others...\r\nMaster\r\nMaster_Windows\r\nSolo\r\ncdn_solo\r\nPatch_Release\r\nQAXDownload\r\n]0;C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1268,"aggregated":"[?25l[2J[m[HProject dir not found, checking others...\r\nMaster\r\nMaster_Windows\r\nSolo\r\ncdn_solo\r\nPatch_Release\r\nQAXDownload\r\n]0;C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe[?25h","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504295424}}
{"type":"message","id":"42c5ce7c","parentId":"8e05b967","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:20.222Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! I see `D:\\Solo` which could be the project directory. But let me reconsider the approach.\n\nThe `cursor agent` doesn't seem to accept piped input well. Let me try a completely different approach:\n\n**Approach: Create a local HTTP server that bridges between me and Cursor**\n\nI'll create a script that:\n1. Opens a local WebSocket/HTTP server\n2. Spawns `cursor agent` connected to a terminal multiplexer (like `screen` or `tmux`)\n3. Accepts instructions from me via HTTP and sends them to cursor agent\n4. Returns cursor agent's output back to me\n\nBut this is getting complex. Let me check if there's a simpler way.\n\nActually, let me step back and look at this from the user's perspective:\n- They want: Phone → Feishu → OpenClaw → Cursor → execute task\n- The most reliable way: I write a task description to a file → Cursor agent picks it up\n\nLet me check if Cursor has any kind of \"watch for task files\" mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_14PqY5rIq85psNhBFnN15383","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 找月圆之夜项目目录\nGet-ChildItem \"D:\\Solo\" -Name -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 10\n# 看看有没有 .cursor 配置\nTest-Path \"D:\\Solo\\.cursor\"\n# 检查 Cursor 配置文件\nGet-Content \"$env:APPDATA\\Cursor\\User\\settings.json\" -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 50","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":169,"output":381,"cacheRead":130688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131238,"cost":{"input":0.00002366,"output":0.00010668,"cacheRead":0.0036592639999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003789604}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504295426,"responseId":"9d21f9d1-55c8-4a9f-95ff-a16965295118"}}
