{"type":"message","id":"1ec2a762","parentId":"a36c7bfd","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:27.436Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that `D:\\Solo` exists as a root directory but there's no `.cursor` there. The project `e-Solo-nightoffullmoon` in `.cursor/projects` is probably the one.\n\nLet me take yet another approach. Let me check if I can use `--add-mcp` to register OpenClaw as an MCP server that Cursor can see, and then create an MCP tool that allows me to send tasks. But that's Cursor → OpenClaw, not the other way.\n\nOK, let me think about this more practically. The user wants to send instructions from their phone to Cursor. The simplest bridge that will actually work is:\n\n**Write a bridge script** that I can interact with via PTY. The script:\n1. Takes the instruction as a command-line argument\n2. Opens `cursor project_dir` with the instruction\n3. Or sends it via some other mechanism\n\nActually, let me try one more thing - maybe `cursor -g` can be used to open the cursor chat with a message.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EDoXuiJYRcz3IuL9rTbv0473","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 试试 cursor --goto 配合文件\n# 先看看 Cursor 的工作区/项目配置\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\projects\\e-Solo-nightoffullmoon\" -Recurse -Name 2>$null\n\nWrite-Output \"=== Also check what projects exist ===\"\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\projects\" -Directory | % {\n    $projFile = Join-Path $_.FullName \"project.json\"\n    if (Test-Path $projFile) {\n        $proj = Get-Content $projFile -Raw\n        Write-Output \"$($_.Name): $proj\"\n    } else {\n        Write-Output \"$($_.Name): (no project.json)\"\n    }\n}","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":69,"output":447,"cacheRead":131200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131716,"cost":{"input":0.00000966,"output":0.00012516,"cacheRead":0.0036736,"cacheWrite