{"type":"message","id":"8c5dc0fa","parentId":"1ec2a762","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:27.716Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_EDoXuiJYRcz3IuL9rTbv0473","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"mcps\r\nterminals\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\INSTRUCTIONS.md\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\SERVER_METADATA.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\create_project.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\move_agent_to_cloned_root.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\move_agent_to_root.json\r\n=== Also check what projects exist ===\r\n1779098020649: (no project.json)\r\n1779099305554: (no project.json)\r\nC-Users-yyzypublic-AppData-Local-Temp-dfb05b96-d2df-4ff4-9348-634112cde6a9: (no project.json)\r\nC-Users-yyzypublic-AppData-Local-Temp-f952063c-fe7c-47c9-b4e7-6305cb7c1e27: (no project.json)\r\ne-Solo-nightoffullmoon: (no project.json)\r\nempty-window: (no project.json)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":268,"aggregated":"mcps\r\nterminals\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\INSTRUCTIONS.md\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\SERVER_METADATA.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\create_project.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\move_agent_to_cloned_root.json\r\nmcps\\cursor-app-control\\tools\\move_agent_to_root.json\r\n=== Also check what projects exist ===\r\n1779098020649: (no project.json)\r\n1779099305554: (no project.json)\r\nC-Users-yyzypublic-AppData-Local-Temp-dfb05b96-d2df-4ff4-9348-634112cde6a9: (no project.json)\r\nC-Users-yyzypublic-AppData-Local-Temp-f952063c-fe7c-47c9-b4e7-6305cb7c1e27: (no project.json)\r\ne-Solo-nightoffullmoon: (no project.json)\r\nempty-window: (no project.json)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504307716}}
{"type":"message","id":"707bc7f3","parentId":"8c5dc0fa","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:31.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so Cursor projects are identified by path-hash names. `e-Solo-nightoffullmoon` likely corresponds to a project on drive E or D. Let me find the actual project path and look at the Cursor MCP server metadata to understand what tools are available.\n\nLet me check the `cursor-app-control` MCP - this is the MCP server that Cursor itself provides for controlling the IDE from agents.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BgEycpBStMtcWpQht68p0570","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\projects\\e-Solo-nightoffullmoon\\mcps\\cursor-app-control\\SERVER_METADATA.json\" -Raw\nWrite-Output \"===\"\nGet-Content \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\projects\\e-Solo-nightoffullmoon\\mcps\\cursor-app-control\\INSTRUCTIONS.md\" -Raw","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":268,"output":231,"cacheRead":131712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132211,"cost":{"input":0.00003752,"output":0.00006468000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0036879359999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003790136}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504307719,"responseId":"66464ca9-d676-4201-8c2f-889756431ddc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0024873","parentId":"707bc7f3","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:31.449Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_BgEycpBStMtcWpQht68p0570","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"serverIdentifier\": \"cursor-app-control\",\n  \"serverName\": \"cursor-app-control\"\n}\r\n===\r\nThe cursor-app-control MCP allows you to control the Cursor application itself. Use it to:\n- Move the current agent to a new root workspace directory (move_agent_to_root) 鈥?use this after creating a worktree or whenever the conversation should continue from a different workspace root\n- Move the current agent to a verbatim clone of the current workspace (move_agent_to_cloned_root) 鈥?use this ONLY when the target is a sibling clone already on the agent's branch (for example from cursorfs-clone); skips the migration git fetch / ff-merge that the generic move performs\n- Create a new project at a given path (create_project) 鈥?creates the directory if missing and initializes a git repository. Use this to bootstrap a new project before moving to it with move_agent_to_root\n- Open a resource by URI in Glass (open_resource) 鈥?opens files in the right-hand editor panel (workspace paths or anything under ~/.cursor), focuses terminals, opens output channels, opens web links according to the Glass browser setting, or delegates other schemes to the default workbench opener\n- Manage personal rules in Cursor Settings (manage_personal_rules) 鈥?list, add, update, or delete user rules after asking what the user wants Cursor to remember\n\nUse move_agent_to_root when you want the current conversation to adopt a different root workspace directory. This updates the visible work surface and the default cwd for new terminals.\nUse move_agent_to_cloned_root when the target is a freshly-made sibling clone of the current workspace.\nUse create_project when you need to create a brand new project directory with an initialized git repository.\nUse open_resource when you need to reveal a file, terminal, output channel, or URL for the current agent.\nUse manage_personal_rules for onboarding and preference-learning workflows. Always list first to avoid duplicate memories, and only write rules the user has agreed should be remembered."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":212,"aggregated":"{\n  \"serverIdentifier\": \"cursor-app-control\",\n  \"serverName\": \"cursor-app-control\"\n}\r\n===\r\nThe cursor-app-control MCP allows you to control the Cursor application itself. Use it to:\n- Move the current agent to a new root workspace directory (move_agent_to_root) 鈥?use this after creating a worktree or whenever the conversation should continue from a different workspace root\n- Move the current agent to a verbatim clone of the current workspace (move_agent_to_cloned_root) 鈥?use this ONLY when the target is a sibling clone already on the agent's branch (for example from cursorfs-clone); skips the migration git fetch / ff-merge that the generic move performs\n- Create a new project at a given path (create_project) 鈥?creates the directory if missing and initializes a git repository. Use this to bootstrap a new project before moving to it with move_agent_to_root\n- Open a resource by URI in Glass (open_resource) 鈥?opens files in the right-hand editor panel (workspace paths or anything under ~/.cursor), focuses terminals, opens output channels, opens web links according to the Glass browser setting, or delegates other schemes to the default workbench opener\n- Manage personal rules in Cursor Settings (manage_personal_rules) 鈥?list, add, update, or delete user rules after asking what the user wants Cursor to remember\n\nUse move_agent_to_root when you want the current conversation to adopt a different root workspace directory. This updates the visible work surface and the default cwd for new terminals.\nUse move_agent_to_cloned_root when the target is a freshly-made sibling clone of the current workspace.\nUse create_project when you need to create a brand new project directory with an initialized git repository.\nUse open_resource when you need to reveal a file, terminal, output channel, or URL for the current agent.\nUse manage_personal_rules for onboarding and preference-learning workflows. Always list first to avoid duplicate memories, and only write rules the user has agreed should be remembered.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504311449}}
{"type":"message","id":"203a86bb","parentId":"d0024873","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:36.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so this is about controlling Cursor from within Cursor's own agent. Not directly helpful for my use case.\n\nLet me think about this from a completely different angle. The simplest bridge that works:\n\n**Approach: Use `cursor --goto` to open a file with content, then the user manually triggers Cursor agent**\n\nBut the user wants Cursor to actually execute tasks, not just open files.\n\n**What if I use PowerShell to start cursor agent in a new window and send keystrokes?**\n\nOr...\n\n**The real answer: register OpenClaw as an MCP server that Cursor can call, and implement a \"pending task\" mechanism.**\n\nActually, the simplest approach that would actually work:\n\n1. I write a \"Cursor Bridge\" skill for OpenClaw\n2. The bridge writes task files to a location Cursor monitors\n3. Cursor's agent watches for these tasks and executes them\n\nLet me check if Cursor has a file-based task mechanism.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_upWPmL7EImkZs2DBe9Ao7250","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看 Cursor 有没有任务队列或类似机制\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\" -Recurse -Name -Filter \"*.md\" | Select-Object -First 20\nWrite-Output \"===\"\nGet-ChildItem \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\" -Recurse -Name -Filter \"*.json\" | Select-Object -First 20","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":565,"output":345,"cacheRead":132096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133006,"cost":{"input":0.00007910000000000001,"output":0.0000966,"cacheRead":0.003698688,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003874388}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504311452,"responseId":"31a612c1-fadc-4709-80ff-27e3b2092603"}}
