{"type":"message","id":"78150465","parentId":"51034d5c","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:43.092Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! I see `open_automation.json` in the `empty-window` project. There's also a `rename_chat.json`. These are MCP tools available within Cursor.\n\nLet me take a completely different and more practical approach. Rather than trying to directly interface with `cursor agent` via pipe, I'll:\n\n1. **Create an OpenClaw skill called `cursor-bridge`** that provides the bridge service\n2. The bridge will:\n   - Start a local WebSocket server that Cursor can connect to via MCP (registering as an MCP server)\n   - OR use a simpler approach: write task files to a watched location and notify via Cursor's mechanism\n\nActually, wait. Let me think about the simplest thing that would actually work:\n\n**`cursor agent` approach**: I spawn `cursor agent` as a persistent background process and communicate with it through its stdin/stdout. The key question is whether cursor agent reads from stdin after startup.\n\nLet me try a different test - create a script that starts cursor agent and feeds it commands.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9ZwudPYwdzIaR2RzFdYS1259","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 试试用 Start-Process + stdin redirect 的方式\n# 创建一个输入文件\n@\"\n请列出当前目录的所有文件，然后告诉我你的工作目录是什么\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath \"$env:TEMP\\cursor_input.txt\" -Encoding utf8\n\n# 启动 cursor agent 并重定向输入\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = \"cursor\"\n$psi.Arguments = \"agent\"\n$psi.RedirectStandardInput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n\n$p = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 1\n\n# 写指令到 stdin\n$p.StandardInput.WriteLine(\"请列出当前目录的文件，然后告诉我你的工作目录是哪里\")\n$p.StandardInput.Flush()\nStart-Sleep -Seconds 5\n\n# 尝试读取输出\ntry {\n    $output = $p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    Write-Output \"OUTPUT: $output\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Output \"Read error: $_\"\n}\n\n$p.Kill()","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":805,"output":546,"cacheRead":132992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134343,"cost":{"input":0.0001127,"output":0.00015288,"cacheRead":0.003723776,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0039893559999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504316636,"responseId":"bf85ec81-2dba-4566-a099-b9257ca7b4fe"}}
