{"type":"message","id":"e74e4558","parentId":"783566ce","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:18:53.780Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process didn't start because `cursor` command can't be found by `Process.Start`. Let me use the full path. But actually, let me take a step back and think about what will work.\n\nLet me try a different, more practical approach. I'll create a small Node.js bridge script that:\n1. Spawns `cursor agent` as a child process\n2. Connects to its stdin/stdout\n3. Listens on stdin for instructions\n\nThen I can run the bridge as a PTY and pipe instructions to it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Cr8qnT1TfRoIkBknhp6q8625","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 用 node 来管理 cursor 子进程\nnode -e \"\nconst { spawn } = require('child_process');\nconst cursor = spawn('cursor', ['agent'], {\n  stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n  env: { ...process.env }\n});\n\nlet output = '';\ncursor.stdout.on('data', d => { output += d.toString(); });\ncursor.stderr.on('data', d => { output += d.toString(); });\n\n// Send instruction\ncursor.stdin.write('请列出当前目录的文件结构，只回复第一行\\n');\ncursor.stdin.end();\n\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  console.log('OUTPUT:', output.substring(0, 2000));\n  cursor.kill();\n  process.exit(0);\n}, 10000);\n\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":438,"output":332,"cacheRead":134272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135042,"cost":{"input":0.00006132,"output":0.00009296,"cacheRead":0.003759616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003913896}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504329436,"responseId":"35c1cb46-8d76-4d2a-87dd-529b61d22be5"}}
