{"type":"message","id":"c8054e70","parentId":"43d6a0b9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:19:12.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The PATH includes `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\bin` which is where `cursor.cmd` lives. But `cmd.exe` is in `C:\\Windows\\System32` which is also in the PATH. So `spawn cmd.exe` should work...\n\nWait, the error was `ENOENT` for `cmd.exe`. This is very odd. Let me try with the full path to cmd.exe.\n\nActually, I notice the OpenClaw session runs in a restricted environment. The `exec` tool might be running in a sandbox or with a modified environment. Let me try using the exec tool directly instead of running through Node.js' spawn.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KYKFxinVmgPMJXYKJEtT4442","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use exec tool directly with cursor agent via PTY\n$env:CURSOR_AGENT_NO_GUI = \"1\"\n$msg = \"列出D:\\Solo目录下的文件，最多5个\"\nWrite-Output \"Sending to cursor agent: $msg\"\n$msg | & \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\bin\\cursor.cmd\" agent 2>&1","timeout":30,"pty":true}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":307,"output":326,"cacheRead":137088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137721,"cost":{"input":0.000042980000000000005,"output":0.00009128000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0038384639999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0039727239999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504347890,"responseId":"51a71b4d-62a4-4e63-917a-59e86f9c88ae"}}
