{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6dcdd0a7a8b8b3bd4c750c97ec0\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"sender\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-06-15 14:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Yousan(叶枝君) (ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"name\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"70d866f5","parentId":"119b57de","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:21:32.257Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"6788aa16","parentId":"70d866f5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:21:44.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user chose option A - the Node.js PTY bridge script. Let me build this.\n\nThe plan:\n1. Install `node-pty` (or find a Windows-compatible alternative for creating a pseudo-terminal)\n2. Create a bridge script that:\n   - Starts `cursor agent` in a pseudo-terminal\n   - Runs an HTTP server for receiving tasks\n   - When a task comes in, sends it to cursor agent via the PTY\n   - Collects output and returns it\n3. Package it as an OpenClaw skill\n\nLet me first check if `node-pty` works on this Windows system, or if there's a better alternative.\n\nActually, let me think about the architecture more carefully:\n\nThe bridge needs to:\n1. **Start cursor agent** in a pseudo-terminal\n2. **Listen on a local port** for incoming task requests (from me)\n3. **Forward tasks** to cursor agent via the PTY\n4. **Capture output** from cursor agent\n5. **Return results**\n\nFor Windows, `node-pty` uses `winpty` under the hood. Another option is `conpty` which is built into Windows 10+ (this system is Windows 10 22631 - 23H2).\n\nLet me check what's available and create the bridge.\n\nActually, I should create this as an OpenClaw skill first (using the skill-creator approach), then implement it. Let me think about the skill structure:\n\n```\ncursor-bridge/\n├── SKILL.md\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── bridge_server.mjs    # Main bridge HTTP+PTY server\n│   └── (run as background process)\n└── references/\n    └── setup.md\n```\n\nLet me first check if node-pty is available or can be installed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WRAvpxsPYAhFimwilusT6329","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 node-pty 是否可用\nnode -e \"require('node-pty')\" 2>&1\n\n# 也看看其他 pty 方案\nnode -e \"\n// Check if conpty is available via native node\nconsole.log('platform:', process.platform);\nconsole.log('arch:', process.arch);\nconsole.log('version:', process.version);\n\" 2>&1\n\n# 看有没有 winpty\nGet-Command winpty -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Source\nGet-Command conpty -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Source","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":25001,"output":557,"cacheRead":108032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133590,"cost":{"input":0.00350014,"output":0.00015596000000000002,"cacheRead":0.003024896,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006680996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504492257,"responseId":"447cb6a0-7690-4093-9445-508f2ef8e37d"}}
