{"type":"message","id":"feed651f","parentId":"a3d16cf5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:21:50.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`node-pty` is not installed. Let me install it and also check if it compiles on Windows (it often needs native compilation tools). If it doesn't work, I'll use an alternative approach.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the architecture. Instead of using `node-pty`, I can use a different approach:\n\n**Alternative: Use Windows Terminal's ConPTY API directly**\n\nWindows 10+ has built-in ConPTY (pseudo console) support. I can use `conpty` or `winpty` via a native module, but there's a simpler approach:\n\n**Use `node-pty` as the primary, fallback to `conpty` via node's built-in capabilities**\n\nOr even simpler:\n\n**Use a Node.js child_process with `detached: true` and pipe stdin/stdout**\n\nThe problem was that `cursor agent` doesn't work well with pipe. But maybe I can try with `conpty.js` or use the `spawn` with proper TTY emulation.\n\nActually, let me just install `node-pty` and see if it works.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4ccGHaHooKLaSCJnQkFm7200","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 安装 node-pty\ncd \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\"\nnpm install node-pty 2>&1","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":548,"output":317,"cacheRead":133504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134369,"cost":{"input":0.00007672000000000001,"output":0.00008876000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003738112,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003903592}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504504928,"responseId":"24f579e5-0b8a-4f49-8476-67c1c0180d53"}}
