{"type":"message","id":"56f2947b","parentId":"a7e7a6a4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:22:20.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me create the skill. I'll start by creating the skill directory and then writing the bridge script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_HIuVdBhIVxmG1Yxoqrlw4874","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 创建技能目录\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\scripts\" | Out-Null\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\references\" | Out-Null\n\n# 安装必要依赖\ncd \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\"\nnpm init -y --silent 2>$null\nnpm install node-pty 2>&1\nWrite-Output \"Dependencies installed\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":19,"output":216,"cacheRead":136704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136939,"cost":{"input":0.0000026600000000000004,"output":0.000060480000000000004,"cacheRead":0.003827712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003890852}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504537201,"responseId":"caa52cb3-6498-4927-babb-b0b42c70bfd8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"32976932","parentId":"56f2947b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:22:21.801Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_HIuVdBhIVxmG1Yxoqrlw4874","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wrote to C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\package.json:\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"cursor-bridge\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" && exit 1\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"type\": \"commonjs\"\n}\n\n\n\nadded 2 packages, and audited 3 packages in 715ms\n\nfound 0 vulnerabilities\nDependencies installed"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1561,"aggregated":"Wrote to C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\package.json:\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"cursor-bridge\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"main\": \"index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"test\": \"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" && exit 1\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [],\n  \"author\": \"\",\n  \"license\": \"ISC\",\n  \"type\": \"commonjs\"\n}\n\n\n\nadded 2 packages, and audited 3 packages in 715ms\n\nfound 0 vulnerabilities\nDependencies installed","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504541801}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0840cfa","parentId":"32976932","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:22:48.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the bridge script. This is the core component. It needs to:\n\n1. Start cursor agent in a PTY (node-pty)\n2. Run an HTTP server\n3. Accept task instructions via POST\n4. Forward to cursor agent\n5. Collect output\n6. Return result\n\nKey considerations:\n- cursor agent might take a while to start up\n- Need to handle the PTY output correctly - cursor agent might send ANSI escape codes\n- Need a way to know when cursor agent is done processing\n- Should handle multiple requests (queue them)\n- Need to keep the PTY session alive between requests\n\nLet me also think about a simpler alternative: instead of PTY, what if I use `node-pty` to spawn `cmd.exe` and then call `cursor agent` inside it? \n\nActually, the simplest reliable approach is:\n1. Spawn `cursor agent` in a PTY \n2. This gives us a terminal-based Cursor agent that reads/writes to the PTY\n3. Send instructions via PTY.write()\n4. Read responses via PTY.onData()\n\nBut there are challenges:\n- `cursor agent` is interactive - it shows a prompt, waits for input\n- I need to detect when it's done processing (e.g., look for the prompt pattern)\n- ANSI escape codes need to be stripped\n\nLet me design the script more carefully:\n\n```javascript\n// The PTY session with cursor agent is persistent\n// When a task comes in:\n// 1. Send the instruction to cursor agent\n// 2. Wait for the agent to respond (look for status indicators)\n// 3. After a timeout or completion signal, return the output\n\n// For simplicity:\n// - Wait 1s after sending instruction for agent to process\n// - Capture all output\n// - Strip ANSI codes\n// - Return result\n```\n\nActually, I realize there might be an issue. The `cursor agent` command might try to open a GUI or interact with the user's desktop. Let me test it with node-pty.\n\nLet me write the script and test it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KzAkFZH8l9l4xoeJWvnf0797","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n/**\n * Cursor Agent Bridge Server\n *\n * Starts cursor agent in a pseudo-terminal and provides an HTTP API\n * to send task instructions and receive results.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   node bridge_server.mjs [--port 18790] [--project \"D:/Solo\"]\n *\n * API:\n *   POST /execute\n *     Body: { \"task\": \"指令内容\" }\n *     Response: { \"success\": true, \"output\": \"...\", \"error\": null }\n *\n *   GET /status\n *     Response: { \"running\": true, \"queue\": 0 }\n */\n\nimport http from 'http';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { spawn } from 'child_process';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);\n\n// Config\nconst PORT = parseInt(process.argv.find(a => a.startsWith('--port='))?.split('=')[1] || process.env.BRIDGE_PORT || '18790', 10);\nlet PROJECT_DIR = process.argv.find(a => a.startsWith('--project='))?.split('=')[1] || process.env.PROJECT_DIR || 'D:/Solo';\n\n// Resolve the project directory\nif (PROJECT_DIR && !fs.existsSync(PROJECT_DIR)) {\n  console.error(`[WARN] Project directory not found: ${PROJECT_DIR}, falling back to workspace`);\n  PROJECT_DIR = process.env.INIT_CWD || process.cwd();\n}\n\n// State\nlet agentProcess = null;  // The cursor agent PTY process\nlet agentReady = false;    // Whether agent is ready for input\nlet outputBuffer = '';     // Accumulated output from agent\nlet taskQueue = [];        // Queued tasks\nlet isProcessing = false;  // Whether a task is currently being processed\nlet lastOutputTime = 0;    // Timestamp of last output\n\n// ANSI escape code stripping\nconst ANSI_RE = /[\\u001b\\u009b][[()#;?]*(?:[0-9]{1,4}(?:;[0-9]{0,4})*)?[0-9A-ORZcf-nqry=><]/g;\nconst CONTROL_RE = /[\\x00-\\x08\\x0b\\x0c\\x0e-\\x1f\\x7f-\\x9f]/g;\n\nfunction stripAnsi(text) {\n  return text.replace(ANSI_RE, '').replace(CONTROL_RE, '').trim();\n}\n\n// Check if cursor agent binary is available\nfunction findCursorBinary() {\n  const candidates = [\n    'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\cursor\\\\resources\\\\app\\\\bin\\\\cursor.cmd',\n    'cursor.cmd',\n    'cursor',\n  ];\n  for (const c of candidates) {\n    try {\n      const result = require('child_process').execSync(`\"${c}\" --version 2>nul`, { encoding: 'utf8', timeout: 5000 });\n      if (result) return c;\n    } catch (_) {}\n  }\n  return candidates[0]; // return default, hope it's in PATH\n}\n\nconst CURSOR_BIN = findCursorBinary();\n\n// Start cursor agent in a managed child process (conPTY via child_process with piped stdio)\nfunction startAgent() {\n  if (agentProcess) {\n    try { agentProcess.kill(); } catch (_) {}\n    agentProcess = null;\n  }\n\n  console.log(`[BRIDGE] Starting cursor agent...`);\n  console.log(`[BRIDGE] Binary: ${CURSOR_BIN}`);\n  console.log(`[BRIDGE] Project: ${PROJECT_DIR}`);\n\n  // We spawn cmd.exe that runs cursor agent to get proper TTY behavior\n  agentProcess = spawn('cmd.exe', ['/c', 'cursor', 'agent'], {\n    cwd: PROJECT_DIR,\n    env: {\n      ...process.env,\n      CURSOR_AGENT_NO_GUI: '1',\n      TERM: 'xterm-256color',\n    },\n    stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n    windowsHide: true,\n  });\n\n  outputBuffer = '';\n  agentReady = false;\n\n  agentProcess.stdout.on('data', (data) => {\n    const text = data.toString();\n    outputBuffer += text;\n    lastOutputTime = Date.now();\n\n    // Check if agent is ready (showing prompt or welcome message)\n    const clean = stripAnsi(text);\n    if (clean.includes('>') || clean.includes('Cursor') || clean.includes('ready') || clean.includes('Agent')) {\n      if (!agentReady) {\n        agentReady = true;\n        console.log(`[BRIDGE] Agent is ready`);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // If processing a task, check if output has stabilized (agent waiting for input)\n    if (isProcessing) {\n      const lines = outputBuffer.split('\\n').filter(l => l.trim());\n      const lastLine = lines[lines.length - 1] || '';\n      // Agent shows a prompt when waiting for input\n      if (lastLine.trim().endsWith('>') || lastLine.trim().endsWith('#')) {\n        // Agent is waiting - task might be done or it's asking a question\n        handleTaskComplete();\n      }\n    }\n  });\n\n  agentProcess.stderr.on('data', (data) => {\n    const text = data.toString();\n    outputBuffer += `[STDERR] ${text}`;\n    lastOutputTime = Date.now();\n  });\n\n  agentProcess.on('error', (err) => {\n    console.error(`[BRIDGE] Agent process error:`, err.message);\n    agentReady = false;\n    setTimeout(startAgent, 5000); // auto-restart\n  });\n\n  agentProcess.on('exit', (code) => {\n    console.log(`[BRIDGE] Agent exited with code ${code}`);\n    agentProcess = null;\n    agentReady = false;\n    setTimeout(startAgent, 5000); // auto-restart\n  });\n\n  // Mark agent as ready after a timeout even if we didn't detect the prompt\n  setTimeout(() => {\n    if (!agentReady && agentProcess) {\n      agentReady = true;\n      console.log(`[BRIDGE] Agent assumed ready (timeout)`);\n    }\n  }, 10000);\n}\n\nfunction handleTaskComplete() {\n  if (!isProcessing) return;\n  isProcessing = false;\n\n  const output = stripAnsi(outputBuffer);\n\n  // Resolve the current task promise\n  if (currentTaskResolve) {\n    currentTaskResolve({ success: true, output });\n    currentTaskResolve = null;\n  }\n\n  // Process next in queue\n  outputBuffer = '';\n  setTimeout(processNextTask, 500);\n}\n\nlet currentTaskResolve = null;\nlet currentTaskReject = null;\n\nfunction processNextTask() {\n  if (isProcessing || taskQueue.length === 0) return;\n\n  const task = taskQueue.shift();\n  isProcessing = true;\n  outputBuffer = '';\n\n  const { instruction, resolve, reject } = task;\n  currentTaskResolve = resolve;\n  currentTaskReject = reject;\n\n  // Send instruction to cursor agent\n  const toSend = `${instruction}\\n`;\n  console.log(`[BRIDGE] Sending task (${instruction.substring(0, 80)}...)`);\n\n  if (agentProcess && agentProcess.stdin.writable) {\n    agentProcess.stdin.write(toSend);\n\n    // Set timeout for task execution\n    taskTimeout = setTimeout(() => {\n      if (isProcessing) {\n        isProcessing = false;\n        const output = stripAnsi(outputBuffer);\n        console.log(`[BRIDGE] Task timed out after 60s`);\n        if (currentTaskResolve) {\n          currentTaskResolve({ success: true, output: output + '\\n\\n[TIMEOUT: 60s reached, partial output returned]' });\n          currentTaskResolve = null;\n        }\n        outputBuffer = '';\n        setTimeout(processNextTask, 500);\n      }\n    }, 60000);\n  } else {\n    console.error(`[BRIDGE] Agent not available`);\n    isProcessing = false;\n    reject(new Error('Agent not available'));\n    setTimeout(processNextTask, 1000);\n  }\n}\n\nlet taskTimeout = null;\n\n// HTTP Server\nfunction startServer() {\n  const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n    // CORS headers\n    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n    res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n\n    if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n      res.writeHead(204);\n      res.end();\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Status endpoint\n    if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url === '/status') {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n      res.end(JSON.stringify({\n        running: agentProcess !== null,\n        ready: agentReady,\n        queue: taskQueue.length,\n        processing: isProcessing,\n        projectDir: PROJECT_DIR,\n        cursorBinary: CURSOR_BIN,\n      }));\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Health check\n    if (req.method === 'GET' && req.url === '/health') {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n      res.end(JSON.stringify({ status: 'ok', timestamp: Date.now() }));\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Execute task\n    if (req.method === 'POST' && req.url === '/execute') {\n      let body = '';\n      req.on('data', chunk => body += chunk);\n      req.on('end', () => {\n        try {\n          const { task } = JSON.parse(body);\n          if (!task || typeof task !== 'string') {\n            res.writeHead(400, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: 'Missing or invalid \"task\" field' }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          if (!agentReady || !agentProcess) {\n            res.writeHead(503, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: 'Agent not ready', queue: taskQueue.length }));\n            return;\n          }\n\n          // Queue the task\n          const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n            taskQueue.push({ instruction: task, resolve, reject });\n          });\n\n          // Start processing if not already\n          if (!isProcessing) {\n            processNextTask();\n          }\n\n          // Wait for result\n          promise.then(result => {\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify(result));\n          }).catch(err => {\n            res.writeHead(500, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: err.message }));\n          });\n\n        } catch (e) {\n          res.writeHead(400, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n          res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: 'Invalid JSON' }));\n        }\n      });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // 404\n    res.writeHead(404);\n    res.end('Not found');\n  });\n\n  server.listen(PORT, '127.0.0.1', () => {\n    console.log(`========================================`);\n    console.log(` Cursor Agent Bridge Server`);\n    console.log(`----------------------------------------`);\n    console.log(` Port:     ${PORT}`);\n    console.log(` Project:  ${PROJECT_DIR}`);\n    console.log(` Cursor:   ${CURSOR_BIN}`);\n    console.log(`----------------------------------------`);\n    console.log(` API:\n   POST http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}/execute\n     { \"task\": \"your instruction\" }\n   GET  http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}/status\n   GET  http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}/health`);\n    console.log(`========================================`);\n  });\n\n  return server;\n}\n\n// Main\nconsole.log(`[BRIDGE] Cursor Agent Bridge starting...`);\nconsole.log(`[BRIDGE] PID: ${process.pid}`);\n\n// Start cursor agent\nstartAgent();\n\n// Start HTTP server\nconst server = startServer();\n\n// Graceful shutdown\nprocess.on('SIGINT', () => {\n  console.log('\\n[BRIDGE] Shutting down...');\n  if (taskTimeout) clearTimeout(taskTimeout);\n  if (agentProcess) {\n    try { agentProcess.stdin.write('exit\\n'); } catch (_) {}\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      try { agentProcess.kill(); } catch (_) {}\n      server.close();\n      process.exit(0);\n    }, 2000);\n  } else {\n    server.close();\n    process.exit(0);\n  }\n});\n\nprocess.on('SIGTERM', () => {\n  process.emit('SIGINT');\n});\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\scripts\\bridge_server.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":255,"output":3336,"cacheRead":136832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140423,"cost":{"input":0.0000357,"output":0.0009340800000000001,"cacheRead":0.003831296,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0048010760000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504541803,"responseId":"7387b664-d454-4e71-ab3a-77de6e74ac00"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c3abfbb","parentId":"c0840cfa","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:22:48.621Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_KzAkFZH8l9l4xoeJWvnf0797","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 10669 bytes to C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\scripts\\bridge_server.mjs"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504568621}}
{"type":"message","id":"549b246a","parentId":"9c3abfbb","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:22:54.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the SKILL.md for the cursor-bridge skill, and then test the bridge server.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_N2iraMzC3a9tO7mRBPTz2984","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\nname: cursor-bridge\ndescription: Bridge between OpenClaw and Cursor IDE. Start/manage the Cursor Agent Bridge server, send tasks to Cursor agent via HTTP API, and receive results. Trigger when user says \"cursor\", \"给cursor发消息\", \"让cursor执行\", or similar requests about sending tasks to Cursor.\n---\n\n# Cursor Agent Bridge\n\nOpenClaw ↔ Cursor 桥接服务。在本地启动一个 HTTP 服务，通过伪终端（PTY）与 Cursor Agent 通信。\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### 启动桥接服务\n\n```bash\nnode plugin-skills/cursor-bridge/scripts/bridge_server.mjs\n```\n\n默认监听 `127.0.0.1:18790`，项目目录为 `D:/Solo`。\n\n### 发送任务\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18790/execute \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"task\": \"找到项目中支付日志相关的代码，检查区服ID字段的逻辑\"}'\n```\n\n### 检查状态\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:18790/status\n```\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n手机飞书 → OpenClaw → POST /execute → bridge_server → PTY → cursor agent → 执行\n                              ↓\n                         返回结果\n```\n\n## API\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | `/execute` | 发送任务指令，等待结果 |\n| GET | `/status` | 查看桥接服务状态 |\n| GET | `/health` | 健康检查 |\n\n### POST /execute\n\nRequest:\n```json\n{ \"task\": \"你的指令\" }\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n{ \"success\": true, \"output\": \"cursor agent 的输出...\" }\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Cursor IDE installed\n- `node-pty` (bundled in skill's node_modules)\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":54,"output":516,"cacheRead":140416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140986,"cost":{"input":0.0000075600000000000005,"output":0.00014448,"cacheRead":0.003931648,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004083688}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504568624,"responseId":"d0464a45-04ce-492c-b863-a819427382f5"}}
