{"type":"message","id":"661e5bb2","parentId":"490fab11","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:24:25.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bridge server started, but `running: false` which means `ptyProcess` is null. The cursor binary was resolved to just `cursor` not the full path. And the project directory went to Documents (the default `cwd` of the Start-Job).\n\nThe issue is that `pty.spawn('cmd.exe', ['/c', 'cursor', 'agent'])` might be failing because:\n1. `cursor` is found as `cursor.cmd` which is a batch file, and `cmd.exe /c` should handle that\n2. But maybe `cursor agent` is trying to open a GUI and failing in a non-interactive context\n3. Or maybe `cursor agent` doesn't work with `cmd.exe` as the shell\n\nLet me check - maybe I should spawn cursor agent directly (not through cmd.exe). The `node-pty` module can spawn processes directly.\n\nActually, the problem might be simpler. Let me check if `ptyProcess.onExit` was called, which would tell us if the agent started and then exited.\n\nLet me also fix the project directory issue and the cursor binary path.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_gWqqyNfyiTYPl7yNtCHm8025","name":"edit","arguments":{"oldText":"// Find cursor binary\nfunction findCursor() {\n  const candidates = [\n    'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\cursor\\\\resources\\\\app\\\\bin\\\\cursor.cmd',\n  ];\n  for (const c of candidates) {\n    try {\n      const r = require('child_process').execSync(`\"${c}\" --version 2>nul`, { encoding: 'utf8', timeout: 5000 });\n      if (r) return c;\n    } catch (_) {}\n  }\n  return 'cursor';\n}\n\nconst CURSOR_BIN = findCursor();","newText":"// Find cursor binary\nconst CURSOR_BIN = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\cursor\\\\resources\\\\app\\\\bin\\\\cursor.cmd';","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\scripts\\bridge_server.mjs"}}],"api":"openai