{"type":"message","id":"9614c0de","parentId":"3dd4aacf","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:25:19.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cursor agent started and immediately exited (exit code 0, signal undefined, output length 0). It didn't produce any output at all. This confirms that `cursor agent` when started in a non-GUI / non-interactive terminal context immediately exits because it detects it's not in a proper terminal.\n\nThis is a fundamental limitation - Cursor's agent command appears to check if it's running in a proper interactive terminal and exits silently if not.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of trying to control cursor agent remotely, I should:\n\n1. **Use the file-based approach (方案 B from earlier)** - write task files and let Cursor's loop agent pick them up\n2. **Use Cursor's MCP** - register as an MCP server and provide a tool that returns pending tasks\n3. **Just open files in Cursor** (`cursor -g file:line`) for simpler tasks\n\nLet me go with the file-based approach since it's the most reliable. I'll write a task to a specific file in the project, and then create a Cursor automation/skill that monitors this file.\n\nActually, thinking about it more, the best practical approach for the \"phone → Feishu → Cursor\" flow that works TODAY is:\n\n1. I write the task to `D:\\Solo\\.cursor\\tasks\\pending.md` (or similar)\n2. The user has Cursor agent running and just needs to ask \"what's in my tasks\" or have a `/loop` that checks\n\nBut I could also try using `cursor --goto` to open a file in Cursor with the instruction. Let me test if `cursor -g` plus `--reuse-window` opens a file in the existing Cursor window.\n\nOr better yet - let me think about this from the user's actual workflow. They're at their PC with Cursor open. When they send a message from their phone, I should:\n1. Write the task to a visible file in the project\n2. Bring Cursor to focus with a task\n\nBut I really want the agent to execute tasks automatically. Let me check if there's a way to do this.\n\nActually, wait. Let me reconsider the `cursor agent` approach. Maybe the issue is that `cursor` is a batch file and `cursor agent` is passed as an argument. Let me try `cursor agent` without PTY pipe... or let me check what Cursor 3.7.19's agent command actually does by looking at its source.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4k7IvwHaynTdOcZBsx1Q3192","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看 cursor.cmd 具体怎么转发的\nGet-Content \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\bin\\cursor.cmd\" | Select-Object -First 20\n\nWrite-Output \"===\"\n\n# 也看看有没有其他脚本\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\bin\" -Name","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":181,"output":680,"cacheRead":150528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151389,"cost":{"input":0.00002534,"output":0.00019040000000000002,"cacheRead":0.004214784,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004430524}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504711000,"responseId":"96a54e89-7c54-4da5-9293-a180562fa223"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b623bde","parentId":"9614c0de","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:25:19.587Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_4k7IvwHaynTdOcZBsx1Q3192","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"@echo off\r\nsetlocal\r\nset VSCODE_DEV=\r\nset ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=1\r\n\"%~dp0..\\..\\..\\Cursor.exe\" \"%~dp0..\\out\\cli.js\" %*\r\nIF %ERRORLEVEL% NEQ 0 EXIT /b %ERRORLEVEL%\r\nendlocal\r\n===\r\ncode-tunnel.exe\r\ncursor\r\ncursor-tunnel.exe\r\ncursor.cmd"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":262,"aggregated":"@echo off\r\nsetlocal\r\nset VSCODE_DEV=\r\nset ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=1\r\n\"%~dp0..\\..\\..\\Cursor.exe\" \"%~dp0..\\out\\cli.js\" %*\r\nIF %ERRORLEVEL% NEQ 0 EXIT /b %ERRORLEVEL%\r\nendlocal\r\n===\r\ncode-tunnel.exe\r\ncursor\r\ncursor-tunnel.exe\r\ncursor.cmd","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781504719587}}
{"type":"message","id":"1fd4cd8d","parentId":"3b623bde","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:25:27.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! `cursor.cmd` sets `ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=1` and runs `Cursor.exe` with `cli.js`. So `cursor agent` translates to:\n\n```\nELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=1 Cursor.exe \"path\\to\\cli.js\" agent\n```\n\nThe `ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE=1` means it runs as a Node.js script inside Electron. The `cli.js` handles the `agent` subcommand.\n\nLet me check what `cli.js` does with the `agent` command. Or, more practically, let me try running `cursor agent` differently - maybe it needs the Electron display to work.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to run `cursor agent` as a background process, why not:\n\n1. Write the task to a `.cursor/tasks/pending.md` file\n2. Use `cursor -g` to open and highlight it\n3. Provide the user with a voice telling them to check\n\nBut wait - the user wants AUTOMATIC execution. Let me think about Cursor Automations. Looking at the Cursor automation skill, Cursor supports automated triggers (git events, schedule, webhook). If I set up a Cursor Automation with a webhook trigger, I can call the webhook from OpenClaw when the user sends a message.\n\nActually wait - in the `automate` SKILL.md output, I saw that Cursor Automations can be triggered by webhooks (`webhook: {}`). This means I can:\n1. Create a Cursor Automation with a webhook trigger\n2. The automation's action is to run a prompt/instruction\n3. When user sends a message, I call the webhook\n4. Cursor Automation executes the task\n\nBut we're running in `local` mode, and Cursor Automation webhooks might only work in cloud mode...\n\nLet me look at this more practically. What actually works right now:\n\n1. **Persistent `cursor agent` session via proper PTY** - I need to figure out why cursor agent exits immediately\n2. **File-based + user opens Cursor** - write task, user sees it\n3. **MCP-based** - register a custom MCP server\n\nLet me try option 1 once more, but this time let me see if it works in a regular terminal emulator.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SkCFK2TLxwvpAiU7Gf9z6625","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 cursor cli.js 的 agent 命令\nGet-Content \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\out\\cli.js\" -Head 20 2>$null\n\n# 看看有没有 agent 相关的文件\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\out\" -Name -Filter \"*agent*\" 2>$null | Select-Object -First 10\nGet-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\node_modules\" -Name -Filter \"*cursor*\" 2>$null | Select-Object -First 10","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":207,"output":720,"cacheRead":151296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152223,"cost":{"input":0.00002898,"output":0.00020160000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0042362879999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004466868}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504719590,"responseId":"d23dc2b1-c67b-465e-b600-4b4bb649a368"}}
