{"type":"message","id":"d50c13d0","parentId":"38e820c6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:25:37.004Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK this is the minified/compiled CLI code. It's not practical to reverse engineer. Let me take a different, more practical approach.\n\nInstead of trying to make `cursor agent` work in headless mode (which it clearly doesn't support), I should pivot to the working approach:\n\n**方案 B: 文件队列 + 用户在 Cursor 中运行 `/loop`**\n\nThis approach:\n1. I write task descriptions to a project file when the user sends a message\n2. The user runs a `/loop` command once in Cursor agent\n3. The loop checks for new tasks and executes them\n4. Results are written back\n\nThis is the most practical and reliable approach. Let me set it up.\n\nActually, let me think of a more elegant approach. What if I create a Node.js script that:\n\n1. Monitors a task directory for new `.md` files\n2. When a new file appears, it formats it as an agent prompt\n3. Opens Cursor with a focused agent panel\n\nActually, the simplest working approach is:\n\n1. I write tasks to `D:\\Solo\\.cursor\\tasks\\pending.md` (with timestamps)\n2. The user has a persistent `cursor agent` session running on their machine\n3. When the user sends a message from phone, I write the task\n\nBut this doesn't automatically execute. Let me think about what's the best UX...\n\nActually, revisiting the Cursor `--add-mcp` option: I can register OpenClaw as an MCP server that Cursor can call. Then the user can configure a Cursor Automation that periodically checks for pending tasks via my MCP server and executes them.\n\nFor example:\n1. I create a simple MCP server that provides a `get_pending_task` tool\n2. The user creates a Cursor Automation with a cron trigger that calls `get_pending_task`\n3. When a task is pending, the automation executes the instruction\n\nThis is actually very elegant. Let me implement this approach.\n\nActually, let me just present the options to the user clearly and let them choose. The most practical approach is:\n\n**方案 B (文件队列)**: I write task files, user keeps a loop running. Simple, no additional setup needed.\n\nLet me implement this now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YX6Q34Y2nX4Ck9YzXiJZ2524","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 创建任务队列目录\nNew-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"D:\\Solo\\.cursor\\tasks\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nWrite-Output \"tasks dir created: $(Test-Path 'D:\\Solo\\.cursor\\tasks')\"\n\n# 写一个测试任务\n@\"\n## Pending Task - $(Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm')\n\n**From:** 叶枝君 (via Feishu)\n**Instruction:** \n\n找到项目中支付日志相关的代码文件，检查区服ID字段(server_id/zone_id)的逻辑\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath \"D:\\Solo\\.cursor\\tasks\\pending.md\" -Encoding utf8\n\nWrite-Output \"Test task written\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":9518,"output":691,"cacheRead":152192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":162401,"cost":{"input":0.00133252,"output":0.00019348000000000002,"cacheRead":0.004261376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005787376}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781504727650,"responseId":"7769b5f9-d1e9-4af6-8d1e-ac26d90416a1"}}
