{"type":"message","id":"08cd0dd3","parentId":"d17b193a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:31:23.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Cursor is running! There are multiple Cursor processes. Since Cursor is based on VS Code, it likely has a VS Code-compatible extension host. I can try to use the VS Code API to communicate with it.\n\nVS Code has:\n1. A CLI interface (`code --command` or similar)\n2. An extension host with IPC\n3. The `commands` API that can be called from VS Code URI handler\n\nLet me check if Cursor supports VS Code's `--command` or has a command URI scheme.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_N6LWsCgGtBRYZStrrlfA2337","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 试试 VS Code 兼容的命令行方式把指令传给 Cursor\n# VS Code 支持 code --command 和 vscode:// URI\n\n# 方法1: 通过 cursor --command 执行命令\ncursor --command \"workbench.action.chat.open\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5\n\n# 方法2: 检查是否有 command 选项\ncursor --help 2>&1 | Select-String \"command\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":345,"output":263,"cacheRead":165760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":166368,"cost":{"input":0.0000483,"output":0.00007364,"cacheRead":0.00464128,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00476322}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505078715,"responseId":"ad6dc808-6e45-4210-91be-a6d2606362cd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"22c197b7","parentId":"08cd0dd3","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:31:27.036Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_N6LWsCgGtBRYZStrrlfA2337","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"cursor : Warning: 'command' is not in the list of known options, but still passed to Electron/Chromium.\r\n所在位置 行:5 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --command \"workbench.action.chat.open\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -F ...\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (Warning: 'comma...ctron/Chromium.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n\r\n                                             '{\"name\":\"server-name\",\"command\":...}\r\n                                          effective only when the command opens\r\n                                          effective only when the command opens\r\nSubcommands"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3539,"aggregated":"cursor : Warning: 'command' is not in the list of known options, but still passed to Electron/Chromium.\r\n所在位置 行:5 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --command \"workbench.action.chat.open\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -F ...\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (Warning: 'comma...ctron/Chromium.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n\r\n                                             '{\"name\":\"server-name\",\"command\":...}\r\n                                          effective only when the command opens\r\n                                          effective only when the command opens\r\nSubcommands","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781505087035}}
{"type":"message","id":"a261e96a","parentId":"22c197b7","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:31:41.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `--command` option. Let me look for the VS Code IPC mechanism. VS Code uses an extension host that communicates via IPC. If I can inject a command through the IPC channel, I could trigger actions in Cursor.\n\nBut this is getting too complex. Let me think of a simpler approach.\n\nOK, I just had a much better idea. Let me look at what Cursor's `--add-mcp` does:\n\n```\n--add-mcp <json>  Adds a Model Context Protocol server definition to the user profile\n```\n\nI can register an MCP server that provides tools like `send_to_cursor_agent`. When the user is in a Cursor agent chat, they can use my MCP tool. But this is still Cursor pulling from me.\n\nBUT - what if we flip the architecture? Instead of me pushing to Cursor, I create an **MCP server** that:\n1. Runs on a local port\n2. Has a tool `execute_task` that accepts a task string\n3. When the user wants to execute a task, they tell Cursor \"use the openclaw MCP tool\"\n4. Cursor calls my MCP tool\n5. I relay the result\n\nThis means the conversation flow is:\n- User sends message on phone\n- I process it (write files, run scripts, etc.)\n- User asks Cursor \"execute the task from openclaw\"\n- Cursor calls my MCP tool\n\nBut this requires the user to manually ask Cursor.\n\nActually, the user said \"实时对话\" (real-time conversation). I think what they mean is:\n1. They send a message on phone (Feishu) to me\n2. I pass it to Cursor\n3. Cursor executes immediately\n4. I get the result and reply to them\n\nThis means I need to be the one initiating the communication with Cursor, not the other way around.\n\nLet me think about what ACTUALLY works right now...\n\nActually, I just had a key insight. The user said \"能实时对话\" (can have real-time dialogue). Maybe what they mean is not that they want to chat with Cursor through me, but that they want their instructions to be executed by Cursor immediately (not on a loop/polling schedule).\n\nFor immediate execution, there are a few options:\n\n**Option 1: MCP bridge (my favorite approach)**\nI create an MCP server. The user registers it in Cursor settings (one-time). When the user wants to send a task, they ask Cursor's agent to use the MCP tool. But this requires the user to be at the computer.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the user's original request: \"目的是在手机上发消息让Cursor执行项目任务\". The goal is: from phone, send message to make Cursor execute project tasks.\n\nThe real-time part means: when they send a message, Cursor should DO IT NOW, not poll after 30 seconds.\n\nFor this, I need a mechanism where when I receive a message, Cursor automatically starts executing. The only way to do this is:\n\n1. **Background `cursor agent`** - If I can keep cursor agent running in a proper terminal, I can send instructions to it in real-time. The problem is cursor agent exits in non-interactive mode.\n\n2. **Named pipe / file trigger** - Write a task, then trigger Cursor to notice it immediately.\n\n3. **Windows UI automation** - Use Windows APIs to send keystrokes to Cursor's window.\n\n4. **Cursor Extension API** - Write a Cursor extension that opens a local socket and listens for tasks.\n\n5. **`--add-mcp` with notification** - Register an MCP server with a resource that the agent watches.\n\nLet me try approach 3 - use Windows API to bring Cursor to front and inject text. Or approach 4 - simpler: write a Cursor-compatible extension.\n\nActually, the SIMPLEST thing that works is:\n\n**Use `--add-mcp` to register OpenClaw as an MCP server, then when user messages come in, I write to a file that the MCP tool exposes.**\n\nBut this still requires the user to ask Cursor.\n\nOK let me try yet another angle. What if I:\n\n1. Start `cursor agent` in a real, visible terminal window using `Start-Process`\n2. The window stays open because it's a real user-facing terminal\n3. I use Windows API to write to that terminal's input buffer\n\nActually, `cursor agent` in a real terminal window WOULD work because it has a real TTY. Let me test this!\n\nI'll use `Start-Process` to open a new Command Prompt running `cursor agent`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cG8j2bn0NmPp42AsMNb89410","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 开一个新的 cmd 窗口运行 cursor agent (真的窗口)\nStart-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/k cursor agent' -WindowStyle Normal\n\nWrite-Output \"Started cursor agent in a new window. PID:\"\nGet-Process -Name \"cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date).AddSeconds(-15) } | Select-Object Id, StartTime\nGet-Process -Name \"cmd\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date).AddSeconds(-15) } | Select-Object Id, StartTime","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":263,"output":1181,"cacheRead":166272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":167716,"cost":{"input":0.00003682,"output":0.00033068,"cacheRead":0.004655616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005023115999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505087039,"responseId":"a6dce17f-3e1f-481f-9305-6aab3188398f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d94fb82f","parentId":"a261e96a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:31:41.722Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_cG8j2bn0NmPp42AsMNb89410","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Started cursor agent in a new window. PID:\r\n\r\n   Id StartTime         \r\n   -- ---------         \r\n 8764 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n14584 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n21816 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n31912 2026/6/15 14:31:29\r\n32176 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n32460 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n32952 2026/6/15 14:31:28\r\n37280 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n 9340 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n36508 2026/6/15 14:31:40"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":362,"aggregated":"Started cursor agent in a new window. PID:\r\n\r\n   Id StartTime         \r\n   -- ---------         \r\n 8764 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n14584 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n21816 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n31912 2026/6/15 14:31:29\r\n32176 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n32460 2026/6/15 14:31:27\r\n32952 2026/6/15 14:31:28\r\n37280 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n 9340 2026/6/15 14:31:41\r\n36508 2026/6/15 14:31:40","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781505101722}}
{"type":"message","id":"25e5f37a","parentId":"d94fb82f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:31:49.900Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cursor agent started in a new window. But I can't see if it's working from here. Let me check by looking at its process and trying to send keystrokes to the window.\n\nActually, I realize this opens a VISIBLE cmd window on the user's desktop. They can see it and interact with it. But I need to be able to send instructions TO that window from OpenClaw.\n\nFor that, I can use Windows API to:\n1. Find the window handle (by title or PID)\n2. Send keystrokes to it\n3. Read the content from it\n\nThis is possible using:\n- `[System.Windows.Forms.SendKeys]` or `user32.dll` for sending keystrokes\n- `Get-Process` to find the window\n- `[System.Windows.Automation]` for reading content (more complex)\n\nLet me test sending a keystroke to the cursor agent window.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_eq7TvMceBRDhc74UqQHo8005","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 找到 cursor agent 所在的 cmd 窗口\n# 查找标题含 \"cursor\" 或 \"agent\" 的 cmd 窗口\nAdd-Type @\"\nusing System;\nusing System.Runtime.InteropServices;\nusing System.Text;\npublic class WindowHelper {\n    [DllImport(\"user32.dll\", SetLastError = true, CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\n    public static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, StringBuilder text, int count);\n    \n    [DllImport(\"user32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\n    public static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n    \n    [DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\n    public static extern IntPtr FindWindow(string lpClassName, string lpWindowName);\n    \n    [DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\n    public static extern IntPtr FindWindowEx(IntPtr parent, IntPtr child, string className, string windowName);\n    \n    [DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\n    public static extern int SendMessage(IntPtr hWnd, int msg, int wParam, string lParam);\n    \n    public static string GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd) {\n        int len = GetWindowTextLength(hWnd) + 1;\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(len);\n        GetWindowText(hWnd, sb, len);\n        return sb.ToString();\n    }\n}\n\"@\n\n# List all windows with \"cursor\" or \"cmd\" in title\n$shell = New-Object -ComObject Shell.Application\n$shell.Windows() | ForEach-Object {\n    $title = $_.Document.Title\n    if ($title -match \"cursor|agent|cmd\") {\n        Write-Output \"Window: $title\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Also try getting all top-level windows\nWrite-Output \"`n=== All windows ===\"\n$sig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")] public static extern IntPtr GetDesktopWindow();\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")] public static extern IntPtr GetWindow(IntPtr hWnd, int uCmd);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")] public static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n'@\n$winApi = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $sig -Name \"WinAPI\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n$desktop = $winApi::GetDesktopWindow()\n$hwnd = $winApi::GetWindow($desktop, 5)\n$windows = @()\nwhile ($hwnd -ne 0) {\n    $sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder 256\n    $winApi::GetWindowText($hwnd, $sb, 256)\n    if ($sb.ToString() -match \"cursor|agent|CMD\") {\n        $windows += [PSCustomObject]@{HWND=$hwnd; Title=$sb.ToString()}\n    }\n    $hwnd = $winApi::GetWindow($hwnd, 2)\n}\n$windows | Format-Table","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":245,"output":900,"cacheRead":167680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":168825,"cost":{"input":0.0000343,"output":0.000252,"cacheRead":0.00469504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00498134}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505101725,"responseId":"b6635db9-292b-4fcf-abd1-7263258a9a6c"}}
