{"type":"message","id":"8487d88c","parentId":"8302be49","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:32:24.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `SendMessage` with `StringBuilder` doesn't work because of parameter type mismatch. Also `$pid` is a read-only variable in PowerShell (it's the built-in `$PID` variable). Let me use a different variable name.\n\nBut regardless, the window handle 267130 might have changed (the window was opened in a previous exec call). Let me try a different approach - use PowerShell's `[System.Windows.Automation]` or just write a Node.js script that uses `node-pty` to interact with the agent.\n\nActually, you know what, let me step back and reconsider. The user wants real-time communication with Cursor. The approach I was trying (SendMessage/keystrokes) is fragile and hacky.\n\nLet me try a fundamentally different approach:\n\n**Use `cursor --add-mcp` to register an MCP server that I run**\n\nWhen I register an MCP server, Cursor's agent can use its tools. But more importantly, the MCP protocol has a notification system. If I provide a tool that Cursor can poll...\n\nActually, the BEST approach is the simplest one that actually works:\n\n**Use `Start-Process` to open cursor agent in a real terminal, then use `node-pty` to write to its stdin**\n\nWait, I tried this earlier and cursor agent didn't produce output. But that was in a background PTY. Let me try a different approach: what if I use `node-pty` with a REAL Windows Console (ConPTY)? Not just a pipe-based PTY, but a real Windows Pseudo Console (ConPTY) that's API-compatible with a real console.\n\n`node-pty` on Windows uses ConPTY (the Windows Pseudo Console API). So it SHOULD work. Let me debug why cursor agent exits immediately.\n\nLet me try running cursor agent directly (not through cmd.exe) in the PTY.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1bsIFujzKCgiOUGZbgfg5690","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const pty = require('node-pty');\n\n// The path to cursor.cmd\nconst cursorCmd = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Programs\\\\cursor\\\\resources\\\\app\\\\bin\\\\cursor.cmd';\n\nconsole.log('=== Test A: node-pty with cursor agent directly ===');\nconst pA = pty.spawn(cursorCmd, ['agent'], {\n  name: 'xterm-256color',\n  cols: 132,\n  rows: 43,\n  cwd: 'D:\\\\Solo',\n  env: Object.assign({}, process.env),\n});\nlet outA = '';\npA.onData(d => { outA += d; console.log('[A]', JSON.stringify(d.substring(0, 200))); });\npA.onExit(({exitCode, signal}) => console.log('[A] exit:', exitCode, 'signal:', signal, 'len:', outA.length));\n\n// Test B: cmd.exe -> where cursor -> cursor agent\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  console.log('\\n=== Test B: cmd.exe /c cursor agent ===');\n  const pB = pty.spawn('cmd.exe', ['/c', 'cursor', 'agent'], {\n    name: 'xterm-256color', cols: 132, rows: 43,\n    cwd: 'D:\\\\Solo',\n    env: Object.assign({}, process.env),\n  });\n  let outB = '';\n  pB.onData(d => { outB += d; console.log('[B]', JSON.stringify(d.substring(0, 200))); });\n  pB.onExit(({exitCode, signal}) => console.log('[B] exit:', exitCode, 'signal:', signal, 'len:', outB.length));\n}, 3000);\n\n// Test C: cmd.exe (no /c), then interactive cursor agent\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  console.log('\\n=== Test C: cmd.exe interactive -> cursor agent ===');\n  const pC = pty.spawn('cmd.exe', [], {\n    name: 'xterm-256color', cols: 132, rows: 43,\n    cwd: 'D:\\\\Solo',\n    env: Object.assign({}, process.env),\n  });\n  let outC = '';\n  pC.onData(d => { \n    outC += d;\n    const clean = d.replace(/\\u001b\\[.*?[a-zA-Z]/g, '').replace(/[\\x00-\\x08\\x0b\\x0c\\x0e-\\x1f]/g, '').trim();\n    if (clean) console.log('[C]', clean.substring(0, 150));\n  });\n  pC.onExit(({exitCode, signal}) => {\n    console.log('[C] exit:', exitCode, 'signal:', signal, 'len:', outC.length);\n  });\n\n  // Wait for cmd prompt, then start cursor agent\n  setTimeout(() => {\n    console.log('\\n[C] Starting cursor agent...');\n    pC.write('cursor agent\\n');\n  }, 2000);\n\n  // After agent starts, send a command\n  setTimeout(() => {\n    console.log('\\n[C] Sending task...');\n    pC.write('list files in D:\\\\Solo directory, max 10 items\\n');\n  }, 8000);\n\n  // Wait and dump all output\n  setTimeout(() => {\n    const clean = outC.replace(/\\u001b\\[.*?[a-zA-Z]/g, '').replace(/[\\x00-\\x0c\\x0e-\\x1f\\x7f-\\x9f]/g, '');\n    console.log('\\n[C FINAL OUTPUT]');\n    console.log(clean.substring(0, 3000));\n    console.log('\\n[C TOTAL LEN]:', outC.length);\n    process.exit(0);\n  }, 15000);\n}, 6000);\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\scripts\\test_pty3.cjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":494,"output":1302,"cacheRead":172800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":174596,"cost":{"input":0.00006916000000000001,"output":0.00036456000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0048384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00527212}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505132144,"responseId":"69dd498a-3bd7-4f22-b4db-4aac92e54920"}}
