{"type":"message","id":"407b170e","parentId":"6f95e900","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:33:05.909Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly:\n\n- **Test A**: Spawn `cursor agent` directly → exit code 0, output length 0. Agent exits immediately.\n- **Test B**: Spawn `cmd.exe /c cursor agent` → exit code 0, output length 0. Same.\n- **Test C**: Spawn `cmd.exe` interactive, then send `cursor agent` command → The command is echoed but produces NO output from cursor agent itself. It just shows the command on screen and returns to prompt.\n\nSo `cursor agent` is designed to spawn an interactive terminal UI. When it's not in a proper Windows console (even PTY is not sufficient), it probably exits silently.\n\nActually wait, looking at Test C more carefully: the cursor command was typed, but where's its output? The output shows:\n```\nD:\\Solo>cursor agent\n```\nAnd then the next line is my typed \"list files...\" command. No agent prompt, no agent output. The agent was typed and seems to have returned immediately.\n\nBut earlier, when I opened `cursor agent` via `Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/k cursor agent'`, I saw a separate window `● agent - Cursor` (HWND: 267130). This means `cursor agent` DOES open when it has a REAL Windows console window.\n\nSo the issue is:\n- `node-pty` creates a ConPTY (Pseudo Console), which looks like a terminal\n- But `cursor agent` might be checking if it has a REAL HWND (window handle), not just a pseudo console\n- When running in a PTY via node-pty, there's no real window, so cursor agent exits\n\nThe solution would be to:\n1. Open a real terminal window with `cursor agent` running in it\n2. Use Windows API to read/write to its console buffer\n\nOR use a completely different approach. Let me check if there's a way to use Windows Console API to attach to an existing console.\n\nActually, the `Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/k cursor agent'` approach worked - it opened a real window. Now I just need a way to communicate with it. Let me use `kernel32` to write to its console input buffer.\n\nActually, I think the simplest approach is:\n1. Start `cursor agent` in a visible cmd window\n2. Use `kernel32!AttachConsole` to attach to that process's console\n3. Then use `WriteConsoleInput` to inject keystrokes\n4. Use `ReadConsoleOutput` to read the output\n\nBut this is getting complex. Let me try with `Start-Process` and then use the `[System.Console]` API. Or even simpler: create a named pipe and have the cursor agent read from it.\n\nWait, actually, there's a much simpler approach:\n\n**Use `cmd.exe /k` to start cursor agent, then use `node-pty` to write to it**\n\nThe issue is that `cursor agent` exits when there's no real window. But `cmd.exe /k cursor agent` keeps the window open even after cursor agent exits. So if I:\n1. Start `cmd.exe /k \"cursor agent\"` in node-pty\n2. The cmd.exe prompt appears\n3. I type `cursor agent`\n4. Cursor agent starts (but might still exit)\n\nHmm, this is the same problem.\n\nLet me try yet another approach: **write to the actual console of the running Cursor Agent window**.\n\nOr actually, the simplest approach is to:\n1. Keep a `cursor agent` running in a VISIBLE terminal window\n2. From Node.js, write to that window's console input\n\nLet me test writing to the console of the already-running cursor agent.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Q5dWfiQLp0ihlsZR7Sxd9507","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use kernel32 to attach to the cursor agent's console and write input\n$consoleSig = @'\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern bool AttachConsole(uint dwProcessId);\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern bool WriteConsoleInput(IntPtr hConsoleInput, INPUT_RECORD[] buffer, uint length, out uint written);\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern bool FreeConsole();\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern IntPtr GetStdHandle(int nStdHandle);\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern bool SetConsoleMode(IntPtr hConsoleHandle, uint dwMode);\n[DllImport(\"kernel32.dll\", SetLastError = true)]\npublic static extern bool PeekConsoleInput(IntPtr hConsoleInput, INPUT_RECORD[] buffer, uint length, out uint read);\n\npublic struct INPUT_RECORD {\n    public short EventType;\n    public KEY_EVENT_RECORD KeyEvent;\n}\npublic struct KEY_EVENT_RECORD {\n    public bool bKeyDown;\n    public ushort wRepeatCount;\n    public ushort wVirtualKeyCode;\n    public ushort wVirtualScanCode;\n    public char UnicodeChar;\n    public uint dwControlKeyState;\n}\n'@\n$kernel32 = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $consoleSig -Name \"Kernel32\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n\n$STD_INPUT_HANDLE = -10\n$ENABLE_EXTENDED_FLAGS = 0x0080\n\n# PID of the cursor agent\n$targetPid = 14584  # one of the cursor processes started by the window\n\n# Try to attach\nWrite-Output (\"Attempting to attach to PID: \" + $targetPid)\n$attached = $kernel32::AttachConsole($targetPid)\nWrite-Output (\"AttachConsole: \" + $attached)\n\nif ($attached) {\n    $hInput = $kernel32::GetStdHandle($STD_INPUT_HANDLE)\n    Write-Output (\"Console input handle: \" + $hInput.ToString())\n    \n    # Set console mode to enable input\n    $kernel32::SetConsoleMode($hInput, $ENABLE_EXTENDED_FLAGS) | Out-Null\n    \n    # Create a key event\n    $keyRecord = New-Object KEY_EVENT_RECORD\n    $keyRecord.bKeyDown = $true\n    $keyRecord.UnicodeChar = 'e'\n    \n    $inputRecord = New-Object INPUT_RECORD\n    $inputRecord.EventType = 1  # KEY_EVENT\n    $inputRecord.KeyEvent = $keyRecord\n    \n    $written = 0\n    $result = $kernel32::WriteConsoleInput($hInput, $inputRecord, 1, [ref]$written)\n    Write-Output (\"WriteConsoleInput: \" + $result + \", written: \" + $written)\n    \n    # Release key\n    $keyRecord.bKeyDown = $false\n    $inputRecord.KeyEvent = $keyRecord\n    $result = $kernel32::WriteConsoleInput($hInput, $inputRecord, 1, [ref]$written)\n    \n    $kernel32::FreeConsole()\n} else {\n    $err = [System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::GetLastWin32Error()\n    Write-Output (\"Win32 error: \" + $err)\n}","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":375,"output":1601,"cacheRead":174848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":176824,"cost":{"input":0.0000525,"output":0.00044828,"cacheRead":0.004895744,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005396524}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505169139,"responseId":"38d700aa-a459-43a7-a946-c27cbb6136a9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb2c3b49","parentId":"407b170e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:33:06.331Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Q5dWfiQLp0ihlsZR7Sxd9507","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Attempting to attach to PID: 14584\r\n方法调用失败，因为 [System.Object[]] 不包含名为“AttachConsole”的方法。\r\n所在位置 行:39 字符: 1\r\nAttachConsole: \r\nWin32 error: 203\r\n+ $attached = $kernel32::AttachConsole($targetPid)\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : InvalidOperation: (:) []，RuntimeException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : MethodNotFound"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":406,"aggregated":"Attempting to attach to PID: 14584\r\n方法调用失败，因为 [System.Object[]] 不包含名为“AttachConsole”的方法。\r\n所在位置 行:39 字符: 1\r\nAttachConsole: \r\nWin32 error: 203\r\n+ $attached = $kernel32::AttachConsole($targetPid)\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : InvalidOperation: (:) []，RuntimeException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : MethodNotFound","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781505186331}}
{"type":"message","id":"fda6985e","parentId":"eb2c3b49","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:33:17.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `Add-Type` failed because the struct definitions have issues (INPUT_RECORD is a union in C++, which requires field offset/layout attributes). Let me try a simpler approach.\n\nActually, let me step way back. I've been going down rabbit holes trying to make `cursor agent` work in headless mode. Let me reconsider what the user actually wants.\n\nThe user wants: **从手机发消息让Cursor实时执行任务**\n\nThe most practical approach that WORKS TODAY:\n\n1. I create a Cursor-compatible extension or use `--add-mcp` to register a tool\n2. The tool exposes a way for the user (via Cursor agent) to fetch my instructions\n3. The user tells Cursor \"go check what OpenClaw wants me to do\"\n4. Cursor calls my tool, gets the instruction, and executes it\n\nBut this requires the user to initiate in Cursor. For real \"push\" from phone...\n\nActually, wait. Let me check if `cursor --add-mcp` supports adding an MCP server that can send notifications to Cursor (not just respond to tool calls). The MCP protocol supports notifications.\n\nBut more practically: **what if I use the Windows clipboard + `cursor agent` in a real window?**\n\n1. I write the instruction to the clipboard\n2. The `cursor agent` window is already open and showing\n3. I bring the window to focus (SetForegroundWindow)\n4. I paste (Ctrl+V) using PostMessage\n5. I send Enter\n\nLet me try this approach using the working `SetForegroundWindow` + PostMessage.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3YBfh619j3H0McQKMJ6t7260","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 更简单的方法：设置剪贴板 + 前台窗口发送按键\n# 先确认 cursor agent 窗口还在\n$agentHwnd = 267130\n\n# 获取窗口标题看看是不是还在\n$sig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\npublic static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr FindWindow(string lpClassName, string lpWindowName);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern bool SetForegroundWindow(IntPtr hWnd);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern bool ShowWindow(IntPtr hWnd, int nCmdShow);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern bool PostMessage(IntPtr hWnd, int Msg, int wParam, int lParam);\n'@\n$user32 = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $sig -Name \"User32A\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n\n# Also search for the agent window by name\n$foundHwnd = $user32::FindWindow($null, \"● agent - Cursor\")\nWrite-Output (\"Found by name: \" + $foundHwnd.ToString())\n\n# Get title\n$len = $user32::GetWindowTextLength($foundHwnd)\n$sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder ($len + 1)\n$user32::GetWindowText($foundHwnd, $sb, $len + 1)\nWrite-Output (\"Title: \" + $sb.ToString())\n\n# Set clipboard\nAdd-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms\ntry {\n    [System.Windows.Forms.Clipboard]::SetText(\"list files in D:\\Solo\")\n    Write-Output \"Clipboard set\"\n} catch {\n    Write-Output \"Clipboard error: $_\"\n    # Alternative: use a temp file\n    \"list files in D:\\Solo\" | Set-Clipboard\n    Write-Output \"Clipboard set via Set-Clipboard\"\n}\n\n# Bring window to front\n$user32::ShowWindow($foundHwnd, 5) | Out-Null\n$user32::SetForegroundWindow($foundHwnd) | Out-Null\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500\n\n# Send Ctrl+V (paste)\n$WM_KEYDOWN = 0x100\n$WM_KEYUP = 0x101\n$VK_CONTROL = 0x11\n$VK_V = 0x56\n\n# Key down sequence: Ctrl down, V down, V up, Ctrl up\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYDOWN, $VK_CONTROL, 0) | Out-Null\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYDOWN, $VK_V, 0) | Out-Null\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 100\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYUP, $VK_V, 0) | Out-Null\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYUP, $VK_CONTROL, 0) | Out-Null\nWrite-Output \"Sent Ctrl+V\"\n\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500\n\n# Send Enter\n$VK_RETURN = 0x0D\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYDOWN, $VK_RETURN, 0) | Out-Null\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 100\n$user32::PostMessage($foundHwnd, $WM_KEYUP, $VK_RETURN, 0) | Out-Null\nWrite-Output \"Sent Enter\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":184,"output":1226,"cacheRead":176768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":178178,"cost":{"input":0.00002576,"output":0.00034328,"cacheRead":0.0049495039999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005318544}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781505186334,"responseId":"2ee4318f-ea89-42c8-b613-846db5e55dc1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"11186d04","parentId":"fda6985e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:33:18.932Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_3YBfh619j3H0McQKMJ6t7260","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found by name: 0\r\n0\r\nTitle: \r\nClipboard set\r\nSent Ctrl+V\r\nSent Enter"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1658,"aggregated":"Found by name: 0\r\n0\r\nTitle: \r\nClipboard set\r\nSent Ctrl+V\r\nSent Enter","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781505198932}}
{"type":"message","id":"9364f6ad","parentId":"11186d04","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:33:29.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The window \"● agent - Cursor\" (HWND: 267130) is no longer valid - `FindWindow` returned 0 (not found). The cursor agent window probably closed after my previous test. Let me start a new one and get its updated HWND.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The approach of starting a visible window and sending keystrokes is fragile and hacky. The window might close, the user might move it, etc.\n\nLet me take a completely different approach. I spent a lot of time on this. Let me present a clean, honest summary to the user about what's possible and what's not, and let them choose the best path forward.\n\nHere's the reality:\n\n1. **`cursor agent` cannot run in headless/background mode.** It requires a real, interactive Windows console window. I've confirmed this through multiple tests.\n\n2. **Windows UI automation (keystrokes/PostMessage)** is possible but fragile - the window might close, handles change, etc.\n\n3. **The `--add-mcp` approach** - I can register OpenClaw as an MCP server that Cursor's agent can call. But this is Cursor-initiated, not OpenClaw-initiated.\n\n4. **The most practical approach for the user's use case (phone → Cursor immediately):** \n   - Keep `cursor agent` running in a stable, persistent terminal window\n   - Use Windows console API to inject commands and read output\n   - OR use the `--add-mcp` approach with a bridge that makes it feel \"push\"\n\nActually, let me try one more thing. The ` --add-mcp` approach could be powerful. If I:\n1. Run an MCP server locally that I control\n2. Register it with Cursor via `cursor --add-mcp`\n3. The MCP server has tools that Cursor can call\n4. When Cursor's agent calls my tool, it gets the instruction\n5. The instruction is the message the user sent from their phone\n\nThis creates a workflow:\n1. User sends message on phone → OpenClaw\n2. OpenClaw writes the task to a buffer\n3. User says to Cursor agent: \"Check openclaw for tasks\"\n4. Cursor calls my MCP tool → gets the instruction → executes it → returns result\n5. I get the result via MCP → reply to user\n\nIt's not \"push\", but for the user it FEELS like push if they just ask Cursor \"check for tasks\" and Cursor does it.\n\nBut wait - even better: what if Cursor has automation that periodically calls my MCP tool? The Cursor Automation system supports cron triggers and git triggers. If I set up an automation that runs every minute and calls my MCP tool...\n\nActually, let me check what actions Cursor Automations support. From the automate skill, it supports running prompts/instructions. So a cron-based automation could run a prompt like \"check openclaw for tasks\" every minute.\n\nBut this is polling again, which the user doesn't want.\n\nOK, let me just present the situation to the user honestly.\n\nActually wait - I just realized I haven't tried one thing: using `cursor agent` with `--stdio` or similar flag. Let me check if there's a non-interactive mode.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Cbz55FpeX65GGqwye0ab5552","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if Cursor has any non-interactive execution mode\n# Try cursor agent with various flags\n$env:ELECTRON_RUN_AS_NODE = \"1\"\n@\"\necho hello\n\"@ | & \"C:\\Program Files\\Cursor\\resources\\app\\bin\\cursor.cmd\" --version 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 3\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Try cursor --compose or other hidden commands ===\"\n# Check the cli.js entry point for available subcommands  \n$cliJs = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\out\\cli.js\"\n# Search for \"agent\" in the CLI code\nSelect-String -Path $cliJs -Pattern '\"agent\"' -SimpleMatch | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":42,"output":9