{"type":"message","id":"056aa6b6","parentId":"d76605d4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:52:33.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"401 Unauthorized on POST - the script needs a CSRF token. GitLab requires CSRF validation for state-changing requests (POST/PUT/DELETE) even with session cookies.\n\nI need to get the CSRF token first. In GitLab, the CSRF token can be extracted from:\n1. The main HTML page's meta tag: `<meta name=\"csrf-token\" content=\"...\">`\n2. Or from the `X-CSRF-Token` header\n\nLet me fetch the GitLab main page to extract the CSRF token.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QQkRE3nC5HGkNIFOoXA02416","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nimport fs from 'fs';\n\nconst COOKIES_FILE = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\gitlab_cookies.json';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, 'utf8'));\nconst cookieStr = cookies.map(c => c.name + '=' + c.value).join('; ');\n\n// Fetch GitLab main page to get CSRF token\nconst res = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com', {\n  headers: { 'Cookie': cookieStr }\n});\nconst html = await res.text();\n\n// Extract CSRF token from meta tag\nconst match = html.match(/<meta name=\\\"csrf-token\\\" content=\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"/);\nif (match) {\n  const csrfToken = match[1];\n  console.log('CSRF Token:', csrfToken);\n  \n  // Save it\n  fs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\gitlab_csrf.json', JSON.stringify({ token: csrfToken }), 'utf8');\n  console.log('Saved to gitlab_csrf.json');\n} else {\n  console.log('CSRF token not found in page');\n  console.log('Page excerpt:', html.substring(0, 500));\n}\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":384,"output":460,"cacheRead":207232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":208076,"cost":{"input":0.00005376,"output":0.00012880000000000001,"cacheRead":0.005