{"type":"message","id":"55fd6e7f","parentId":"4b90d90a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T06:53:06.887Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, not found. But the previous API call returned 409 (already exists). The difference is that the members api might not return him if he's not directly a member but inherited from a group. GitLab has both direct members and inherited members via groups.\n\nLet me try checking all members (including inherited) vs just direct members.\n\nActually, the API endpoint `projects/:id/members/all` should include both direct and inherited members. But the user might not be found because:\n1. The ID 2068 is wrong for this GitLab instance\n2. Or the member exists but the API doesn't show it\n\nWait, let me check - the `search` found 赵嘉浩 with id=2068, but maybe that's a different user in the GitLab instance. Let me verify.\n\nActually, the `search` command returned `赵嘉浩 (@zhaojiahao) id=2068`. And the `add` API returned 409 which means \"already exists\". But checking members doesn't find him. This is contradictory unless:\n1. The member exists via group inheritance (not direct member)\n2. Or the user was added but I'm using a wrong parameter\n\nLet me try the `/members` (not `/members/all`) endpoint to check only direct members. Or maybe the user was added successfully but the 409 was a race condition.\n\nLet me re-verify by checking if 赵嘉浩 is actually already a member.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4Pe28R19O5JflVyTLL3s8413","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"\nimport fs from 'fs';\nconst cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\gitlab_cookies.json', 'utf8'));\nconst cookieStr = cookies.map(c => c.name + '=' + c.value).join('; ');\n\n// Check if user 2068 (赵嘉浩) exists in api\nconst r1 = await fetch('https://git.devcloud.ztgame.com/api/v4/users/2068', {\n  headers: { 'Cookie': cookieStr, 'Accept': 'application/json' }\n});\nconst user = await r1.json();\nconsole.log('User 2068:', JSON.stringify(user, null, 2));\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":149,"output":519,"cacheRead":210432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":211100,"cost":{"input":0.00002086,"output":0.00014532,"cacheRead":0.0058920959999999994,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006058276}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781506379861,"responseId":"27268d6a-463a-4e7c-be18-7a74cfe89f10"}}
