{"type":"message","id":"31ef969d","parentId":"fe21b0d1","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:16:37.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the agent window title isn't matching \"● agent - Cursor\". It might be a different title now, or the window might need more time. Let me check by listing all windows.\n\nActually, let me take a step way back. I've been going in circles. Let me just focus on what will actually work reliably.\n\nThe user wants: **send a message from phone → Cursor does the work automatically, no manual steps.**\n\nThe ONLY reliable way to do this without user intervention is:\n\n1. **Use the IPC pipe** of the running Cursor instance to send commands\n2. **Use `cursor --command`** if it works like VS Code's `code --command`\n\nVS Code supports `code --command <commandId>` and `code --open-url <url>`. Let me check if the `--command` option might be a hidden feature that works even though it shows a warning.\n\nLet me try `cursor --command \"workbench.action.chat.open\"` - even though it shows a warning, it might still work!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_GA79gw2inps7JVCqmdzt6214","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 找到所有窗口标题\nAdd-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms\n\n$sig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr FindWindow(string lpClassName, string lpWindowName);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\npublic static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr GetDesktopWindow();\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr GetWindow(IntPtr hWnd, int uCmd);\n'@\n$win32 = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $sig -Name \"Win32Find2\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n\n# List all windows with interesting titles\n$desktop = $win32::GetDesktopWindow()\n$hwnd = $win32::GetWindow($desktop, 5) # GW_CHILD\n$results = @()\nwhile ($hwnd -ne [IntPtr]::Zero) {\n    $len = $win32::GetWindowTextLength($hwnd)\n    if ($len -gt 0) {\n        $sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder ($len + 1)\n        $win32::GetWindowText($hwnd, $sb, $len + 1)\n        $title = $sb.ToString()\n        if ($title -match \"cursor|agent|cmd|C:\\\\|command|terminal|powershell\") {\n            $results += [PSCustomObject]@{HWND=$hwnd.ToString(\"X\"); Title=$title; PID=0}\n        }\n    }\n    $hwnd = $win32::GetWindow($hwnd, 2) # GW_HWNDNEXT\n}\n\n$results | Format-Table -AutoSize\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Try cursor --command ===\"\ncursor --command \"workbench.action.chat.open\" 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":104,"output":719,"cacheRead":217216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":218039,"cost":{"input":0.000014560000000000001,"output":0.00020132,"cacheRead":0.006082048,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0062979279999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781507788928,"responseId":"6b91e24d-45b9-43c8-b09f-d40802b8fe5d"}}
