{"type":"message","id":"c92bca3f","parentId":"0479b416","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:17:20.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, this script uses `SendKeys` which was \"access denied\" earlier. That's because `System.Windows.Forms.SendKeys` needs to run in a STA (Single Threaded Apartment) mode and the calling process needs to have a message pump.\n\nWhen running from a background node process, PowerShell's SendKeys will also likely fail because there's no Windows message pump available.\n\nLet me think about this differently. Instead of SendKeys, I need to use `user32!SendMessage` to send keystrokes directly. This should work from any process.\n\nLet me write a C# script that:\n1. Finds the Cursor agent window\n2. Sends WM_KEYDOWN/WM_KEYUP for the paste shortcut\n\nActually, the simplest working approach:\n\n1. Find the Cursor window\n2. Find its child window (the input field)\n3. Use `WM_SETTEXT` to set the text\n4. Find the send button and click it\n\nBut this requires knowing the exact window hierarchy of Cursor's agent UI, which is complex.\n\nLet me try a more basic approach: use `user32!SendMessage` with `WM_CHAR` to type each character, then send Enter.\n\nActually, the most reliable way might be to just write to the console input of the Cursor agent window's cmd.exe process. I know the window title is \"Cursor Agents\" not \"● agent - Cursor\". The HWND was 40052 (hex).\n\nLet me check if that window has a console buffer I can write to.\n\nOK actually, I think I've been way overthinking this. Let me try the simplest possible thing: use `PostMessage` to send Ctrl+V (paste) to the Cursor Agents window. The key is to use proper `PostMessage` instead of `SendKeys`.\n\nFirst, find the correct child window within Cursor Agents that can accept text input, then send the paste command there.\n\nLet me try one more approach: use `UIAutomation` (UI Automation) which is designed for this kind of thing.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XAwxeLCJXwUJK3Fgs0TS9398","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try UI Automation to interact with Cursor Agents window\nAdd-Type -AssemblyName UIAutomationClient\nAdd-Type -AssemblyName UIAutomationTypes\n\n$sig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr FindWindow(string lpClassName, string lpWindowName);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\npublic static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n'@\n$user32 = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $sig -Name \"User32UIA\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n\n# Find the Cursor window\n$hwnd = $user32::FindWindow($null, \"Cursor Agents\")\nif ($hwnd -eq [IntPtr]::Zero) {\n    Write-Output \"Cursor Agents not found, trying broader search...\"\n    # List all windows with Cursor in title\n    $proc = Get-Process -Name \"Cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Id, MainWindowTitle\n    $proc | Format-Table\n    exit 1\n}\n\nWrite-Output \"Found Cursor Agents: HWND=$($hwnd.ToString('X'))\"\n\n# Use UI Automation to find all elements\n$root = [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::FromHandle($hwnd)\n$cond = New-Object System.Windows.Automation.ConditionPropertyCondition(\n    [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::IsEnabledProperty, $true)\n\n# Try to find edit/textarea elements\n$editCond = New-Object System.Windows.Automation.PropertyCondition(\n    [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::ControlTypeProperty,\n    [System.Windows.Automation.ControlType]::Edit)\n$edit = $root.FindFirst([System.Windows.Automation.TreeScope]::Descendants, $editCond)\n\nif ($edit) {\n    Write-Output \"Found Edit control!\"\n    $edit.SetFocus()\n    Start-Sleep -Milliseconds 200\n    [System.Windows.Forms.Clipboard]::SetText(\"在编辑棋谱界面增加滑动后退/前进功能\")\n    Start-Sleep -Milliseconds 100\n    # Send Ctrl+V using UI Automation\n    [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::FocusedElement\n    Write-Output \"Focused on edit control\"\n} else {\n    Write-Output \"No Edit control found, trying other types...\"\n    $textCond = New-Object System.Windows.Automation.PropertyCondition(\n        [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::ControlTypeProperty,\n        [System.Windows.Automation.ControlType]::Document)\n    $doc = $root.FindFirst([System.Windows.Automation.TreeScope]::Descendants, $textCond)\n    if ($doc) {\n        Write-Output \"Found Document control!\"\n    } else {\n        Write-Output \"No suitable input control found\"\n        # Dump all controls\n        $walker = [System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker]::ControlViewWalker\n        $node = $walker.GetFirstChild($root)\n        while ($node) {\n            $name = $node.Current.Name\n            $ctrlType = $node.Current.ControlType.ProgrammaticName\n            if ($name -or $ctrlType -match \"Edit|Document|Text|RichEdit\") {\n                Write-Output \"  $ctrlType : $name\"\n            }\n            $node = $walker.GetNextSibling($node)\n        }\n    }\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":60,"output":1256,"cacheRead":220800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":222116,"cost":{"input":0.000008400000000000001,"output":0.00035168000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0061824,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00654248}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781507825465,"responseId":"0c5df898-22bf-4988-b0bf-d721f024fb55"}}
