{"type":"message","id":"502f78ee","parentId":"119b8e20","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:17:30.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"Cursor Agents\" window is not found. Earlier I saw:\n```\nHWND  Title                                   PID\n----  -----                                   ---\n40052 Cursor Agents                             0\n```\n\nBut now the main window title for the Cursor process with window is `Cursor` (PID 12972). The \"Cursor Agents\" window might have been a different view that's since changed or the window handle was from a previous state.\n\nLet me find the `Cursor` main window and try UI Automation on that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_pesCBej3LOXalpyhXaNB1787","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use the Cursor main window\n$sig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr FindWindow(string lpClassName, string lpWindowName);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\npublic static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n'@\n$user32 = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $sig -Name \"User32UIB\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n\n$hwnd = $user32::FindWindow($null, \"Cursor\")\nWrite-Output \"Cursor window HWND: $($hwnd.ToString('X'))\"\n\nif ($hwnd -ne [IntPtr]::Zero) {\n    # Use UI Automation\n    Add-Type -AssemblyName UIAutomationClient\n    Add-Type -AssemblyName UIAutomationTypes\n    \n    $root = [System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement]::FromHandle($hwnd)\n    Write-Output \"Root: $($root.Current.Name) - $($root.Current.ControlType.ProgrammaticName)\"\n    \n    # Find all child controls with interesting names\n    $walker = [System.Windows.Automation.TreeWalker]::ControlViewWalker\n    $node = $walker.GetFirstChild($root)\n    $count = 0\n    while ($node -and $count -lt 50) {\n        $name = $node.Current.Name\n        $ctrlType = $node.Current.ControlType.ProgrammaticName\n        $isEnabled = $node.Current.IsEnabled\n        if ($name -or $ctrlType) {\n            Write-Output \"  [$ctrlType] $name (enabled=$isEnabled)\"\n        }\n        $node = $walker.GetNextSibling($node)\n        $count++\n    }\n    Write-Output \"Total children checked: $count\"\n    \n    # Check actual process windows\n    Write-Output \"`n=== Child windows of Cursor ===\"\n    $childSig = @'\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern IntPtr FindWindowEx(IntPtr parent, IntPtr child, string className, string windowName);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", CharSet = CharSet.Auto)]\npublic static extern int GetWindowText(IntPtr hWnd, System.Text.StringBuilder text, int count);\n[DllImport(\"user32.dll\")]\npublic static extern int GetWindowTextLength(IntPtr hWnd);\n'@\n    $childApi = Add-Type -MemberDefinition $childSig -Name \"ChildAPI\" -Namespace Win32 -PassThru\n    \n    $child = [IntPtr]::Zero\n    do {\n        $child = $childApi::FindWindowEx($hwnd, $child, $null, $null)\n        if ($child -ne [IntPtr]::Zero) {\n            $len = $childApi::GetWindowTextLength($child)\n            if ($len -gt 0) {\n                $sb = New-Object System.Text.StringBuilder ($len + 1)\n                $childApi::GetWindowText($child, $sb, $len + 1)\n                Write-Output \"  Child HWND=$($child.ToString('X')) : $($sb.ToString())\"\n            }\n        }\n    } while ($child -ne [IntPtr]::Zero)\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":173,"output":888,"cacheRead":222080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":223141,"cost":{"input":0.000024220000000000002,"output":0.00024864,"cacheRead":0.00621824,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0064911}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781507841174,"responseId":"07ae3c88-8d77-4438-84b7-21aa32733b14"}}
