{"type":"message","id":"c8fa556a","parentId":"73d8406e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:34:51.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the main extension code. The extension needs to:\n\n1. Start a WebSocket server on startup\n2. When it receives a message (instruction from OpenClaw):\n   - Open the Cursor Agent panel\n   - Focus the input field\n   - Set the text content\n   - Trigger send\n\nFor interacting with Cursor Agent, I'll try several approaches:\n1. `workbench.action.chat.open` - Opens the chat/agent panel\n2. For actually sending text, I can try:\n   - `vscode.commands.executeCommand('cursor.composerChatInputFocus')`\n   - `vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.send')`\n   - Or use the clipboard approach with paste\n\nLet me also look at the VS Code API for interacting with the chat panel. In VS Code 1.90+, there's the chat/agent API.\n\nActually, in VS Code, there's the following for chat:\n- `vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.open')` - Opens chat\n- `vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.send')` - Sends current message\n- `vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.focusInput')` - Focuses input\n\nBut in Cursor, these might be different. Let me write the extension to try multiple command IDs and fall back to clipboard approach.\n\nActually, I realize I can't just \"paste\" into the chat input from an extension because the extension runs in an extension host that might not have access to the chat input DOM.\n\nLet me think about the best approach:\n\n1. **Use Clipboard API** - Copy to clipboard, then use `commands.executeCommand('editor.action.clipboardPasteAction')` to paste\n2. **Use `env.clipboard.writeText()` + focus + paste command**\n3. **Use `window.activeTextEditor` to manipulate text**\n4. **Use the terminal API**\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for Cursor would be to use the `cursor.composerChatService` if it's accessible from the extension. But that's an internal API.\n\nLet me take a different, more robust approach:\n\n**Approach: Write instruction to a file, then use Cursor's CLI to open it**\n\nActually no, that brings us back to the CLI problem.\n\n**Approach: Use the VS Code `window.createWebviewPanel()` to show the extension's own status**\n\nOK let me take the simplest possible approach:\n\n1. The extension starts a WebSocket server\n2. When a message arrives, the extension:\n   a. Opens the Cursor agent panel via command\n   b. Sets the clipboard text\n   c. Uses `commands.executeCommand` to paste and send\n\nLet me write this now and test it. Even if the paste doesn't work, I can fall back to just showing the instruction in a notification that the user can click to auto-fill.\n\nActually, here's an even better idea. VS Code 1.90+ has a Chat API that extensions can use:\n\n```typescript\nvscode.chat.send('instruction');\n```\n\nor\n\n```typescript\nvscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.open', { query: 'instruction' });\n```\n\nLet me check if this works in Cursor. Some Cursor-specific command IDs might include:\n- `cursor.composerChatInputFocus`\n- `cursor.composerChatAddMessage`\n- `cursor.composerChatSend`\n\nLet me write the extension and use try-catch for multiple command IDs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_vCdpwvJmMOOoZ7G8NzSZ8418","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * Cursor Bridge Extension\n *\n * Starts a WebSocket server and listens for instructions from OpenClaw.\n * When an instruction arrives, it automatically opens the Cursor Agent\n * panel and submits the instruction.\n *\n * Install: Copy this folder to ~/.cursor/extensions/cursor-bridge/\n * Restart Cursor to activate.\n */\n\nconst vscode = require('vscode');\nconst WebSocket = require('ws');  // bundled with Cursor/Electron\n\nlet statusBarItem = null;\nlet wss = null;\nlet latestInstruction = '';\n\n/**\n * Try to open Cursor Agent and send an instruction using various methods.\n */\nasync function sendToAgent(instruction) {\n  const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n  channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Sending instruction: ${instruction.substring(0, 100)}...`);\n\n  try {\n    // Method 1: Try Cursor-specific commands first\n    const cursorCommands = [\n      'cursor.composerChatInputFocus',\n      'cursor.composerChatAddMessage',\n      'workspace.action.cursorAgent',\n      'cursorAgent.open',\n      'cursor.chat.openAgentChat',\n    ];\n    \n    let agentOpened = false;\n    for (const cmd of cursorCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Opened agent via: ${cmd}`);\n        agentOpened = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (e) {\n        // Command not found, try next\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Fallback: use standard chat open\n    if (!agentOpened) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.chat.open');\n        agentOpened = true;\n        channel.appendLine('[bridge] Opened agent via: workbench.action.chat.open');\n      } catch (e) {\n        channel.appendLine('[bridge] Failed to open agent: ' + e.message);\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (!agentOpened) {\n      channel.show();\n      channel.appendLine('[bridge] ERROR: Could not open Cursor Agent panel');\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    // Wait for panel to open\n    await sleep(800);\n\n    // Method 2: Set clipboard and paste\n    await vscode.env.clipboard.writeText(instruction);\n    channel.appendLine('[bridge] Clipboard set');\n\n    // Try to paste via command\n    const pasteCommands = [\n      'editor.action.clipboardPasteAction',\n      'cursor.composerChatPaste',\n      'workbench.action.chat.paste',\n    ];\n\n    let pasted = false;\n    for (const cmd of pasteCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Pasted via: ${cmd}`);\n        pasted = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (e) {\n        // Try next\n      }\n    }\n\n    await sleep(300);\n\n    // Try to send via command\n    const sendCommands = [\n      'cursor.composerChatSend',\n      'workbench.action.chat.send',\n      'cursorAgent.send',\n      'workbench.action.terminal.sendSequence',\n    ];\n\n    let sent = false;\n    for (const cmd of sendCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Sent via: ${cmd}`);\n        sent = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (e) {\n        // Try next\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (pasted && sent) {\n      channel.appendLine('[bridge] ✅ Instruction delivered successfully');\n      updateStatus('✅ Connected');\n      return true;\n    } else {\n      channel.appendLine('[bridge] ⚠️  Partial success - instruction is in clipboard');\n      channel.appendLine('[bridge]    Open Cursor Agent and press Ctrl+V to paste');\n      updateStatus('⚠️  Clipboard');\n      return false;\n    }\n\n  } catch (err) {\n    channel.appendLine('[bridge] Error: ' + err.message);\n    updateStatus('❌ Error');\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction sleep(ms) {\n  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nfunction updateStatus(text) {\n  if (statusBarItem) {\n    statusBarItem.text = `$(broadcast) ${text}`;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Start WebSocket server\n */\nfunction startWebSocketServer(port) {\n  try {\n    wss = new WebSocket.Server({ port, host: '127.0.0.1' });\n    const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n\n    channel.appendLine(`[bridge] WebSocket server listening on ws://127.0.0.1:${port}`);\n\n    wss.on('connection', (ws) => {\n      channel.appendLine('[bridge] Client connected (OpenClaw)');\n      updateStatus('🔗 Connected');\n      \n      // Send acknowledgment \n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'connected', version: '1.0.0' }));\n\n      ws.on('message', async (data) => {\n        try {\n          const msg = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n          channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Received: ${JSON.stringify(msg).substring(0, 200)}`);\n\n          if (msg.type === 'instruction' || msg.type === 'execute') {\n            const instruction = msg.instruction || msg.text || '';\n            if (!instruction) {\n              ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Missing instruction field' }));\n              return;\n            }\n\n            latestInstruction = instruction;\n            updateStatus('⏳ Executing...');\n\n            // Send to agent\n            const success = await sendToAgent(instruction);\n\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n              type: 'result',\n              success,\n              message: success ? 'Instruction sent to agent' : 'Instruction copied to clipboard (paste in agent)',\n              instruction,\n            }));\n\n          } else if (msg.type === 'ping') {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'pong' }));\n          } else if (msg.type === 'status') {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n              type: 'status',\n              latestInstruction: latestInstruction || null,\n              agentConnected: true,\n              port,\n            }));\n          }\n        } catch (err) {\n          channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Parse error: ${err.message}`);\n          try {\n            ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: err.message }));\n          } catch (_) {}\n        }\n      });\n\n      ws.on('close', () => {\n        channel.appendLine('[bridge] Client disconnected');\n        updateStatus('📡 Waiting...');\n      });\n\n      ws.on('error', (err) => {\n        channel.appendLine(`[bridge] WebSocket error: ${err.message}`);\n      });\n    });\n\n    wss.on('error', (err) => {\n      channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Server error: ${err.message}`);\n      if (err.code === 'EADDRINUSE') {\n        channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Port ${port} is in use, try restarting Cursor`);\n      }\n    });\n\n    return true;\n  } catch (err) {\n    const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n    channel.appendLine(`[bridge] Failed to start WebSocket server: ${err.message}`);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Extension activate\n */\nfunction activate(context) {\n  const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n  channel.appendLine('[bridge] Cursor Bridge extension activating...');\n  channel.show();\n\n  // Add status bar item\n  statusBarItem = vscode.window.createStatusBarItem(vscode.StatusBarAlignment.Right, 100);\n  statusBarItem.text = '$(broadcast) Starting...';\n  statusBarItem.tooltip = 'Cursor Bridge - OpenClaw integration';\n  statusBarItem.command = 'cursor-bridge.show';\n  statusBarItem.show();\n\n  // Get config\n  const config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration('cursorBridge');\n  const port = config.get('port', 18792);\n\n  // Start WebSocket server\n  const started = startWebSocketServer(port);\n  if (started) {\n    updateStatus(`📡 :${port}`);\n    channel.appendLine(`[bridge] ✅ Ready on ws://127.0.0.1:${port}`);\n  } else {\n    updateStatus('❌ Failed');\n    channel.appendLine('[bridge] ❌ Failed to start');\n  }\n\n  // Register commands\n  const showCommand = vscode.commands.registerCommand('cursor-bridge.show', () => {\n    channel.show();\n    vscode.window.showInformationMessage(\n      `Cursor Bridge: ${latestInstruction ? 'Last instruction: ' + latestInstruction.substring(0, 50) + '...' : 'Waiting for instructions...'}`,\n      { modal: false }\n    );\n  });\n\n  context.subscriptions.push(statusBarItem, showCommand);\n  channel.appendLine('[bridge] Extension activated successfully');\n}\n\nfunction deactivate() {\n  if (wss) {\n    try { wss.close(); } catch (_) {}\n    wss = null;\n  }\n  const channel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n  channel.appendLine('[bridge] Extension deactivated');\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { activate, deactivate };\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\extension\\extension.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":45,"output":2828,"cacheRead":226560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":229433,"cost":{"input":0.000006300000000000001,"output":0.00079184,"cacheRead":0.00634368,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00714182}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781508868312,"responseId":"cb5d9b1c-dfb2-4092-81da-cb907009e54b"}}
