{"type":"message","id":"fd413298","parentId":"4f499dc5","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:37:41.761Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting findings:\n\n1. The extension IS in `~/.cursor/extensions/cursor-bridge/`\n2. `cursor --list-extensions` shows it: `openclaw.cursor-bridge`\n3. The `extensions.json` has it registered:\n```json\n{\"identifier\":{\"id\":\"openclaw.cursor-bridge\"},\"version\":\"1.0.0\",\"location\":{...}}\n```\n\nBut it's missing some key metadata fields that the `anysphere.remote-ssh` extension has:\n- `metadata.isApplicationScoped`\n- `metadata.installedTimestamp`\n- `metadata.source`\n- etc.\n\nThis might mean the extension was detected but not fully activated. The missing metadata might cause Cursor to skip loading it.\n\nAlso, the `cursor-bridge` extension uses `require('ws')` which might not be available in Cursor's extension host. In VS Code, `ws` is bundled with Electron, but it might not be available as a require module for extensions.\n\nLet me check if `ws` is available in Cursor by looking at how the `anysphere.remote-ssh` extension works - it likely uses its own bundled dependencies.\n\nActually, the main issue might be simpler. Looking at the `extensions.json`:\n- The `anysphere.remote-ssh` entry has full metadata including `publisherDisplayName`, `installedTimestamp`, etc.\n- The `openclaw.cursor-bridge` entry is missing almost all metadata fields\n\nThis suggests the extension was discovered (it's in the folder and `cursor --list-extensions` shows it), but it might not be properly activating because:\n1. It might need to be \"installed\" properly (not just copied)\n2. Or the `ws` require is failing silently\n\nLet me modify the extension to not use `require('ws')` - instead, I'll use a built-in HTTP approach or the raw Node.js `net` module which is always available. The `ws` library might not be available in the extension host context.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to use Node.js built-in `net` module to implement a simple TCP protocol instead of WebSocket. Or even simpler: use HTTP (built-in `http` module).\n\nLet me rewrite the extension to use a plain HTTP server instead of WebSocket. This way:\n- No external dependencies needed\n- Built-in `http` module is always available\n- OpenClaw sends POST requests instead of WebSocket messages\n\nThis is more robust.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_GIvLYJ7iySqMIymY0XPE1791","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 验证 ws 是否在 Cursor 的 Electron 里可用\nnode -e \"try { require('ws'); console.log('ws available'); } catch(e) { console.log('ws NOT available:', e.message); }\" 2>&1\n\n# 检查 Cursor 的 Electron 环境\n$cursorExe = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\cursor\\resources\\app\\Cursor.exe\"\nif (Test-Path $cursorExe) {\n    Write-Output \"Cursor.exe found\"\n}","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":682,"output":701,"cacheRead":232704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":234087,"cost":{"input":0.00009548,"output":0.00019628,"cacheRead":0.006515712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006807472}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781509053876,"responseId":"0c4853ce-41d5-4708-98c8-d7268c54a5a7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b0870fe","parentId":"fd413298","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:37:42.473Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_GIvLYJ7iySqMIymY0XPE1791","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ws NOT available: Cannot find module 'ws'\nRequire stack:\n- C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\[eval]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":690,"aggregated":"ws NOT available: Cannot find module 'ws'\nRequire stack:\n- C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\[eval]","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781509062472}}
{"type":"message","id":"a5c3bc31","parentId":"5b0870fe","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:37:58.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `ws` module is not available in plain Node.js, and it's also not available in Cursor's extension host (the extension host is a separate process that only has access to what's bundled or explicitly imported).\n\nInside a VS Code/Cursor extension, you can use:\n1. Built-in Node.js modules: `http`, `net`, `fs`, `path`, etc.\n2. VS Code API: `vscode` module\n3. Modules bundled with the extension itself\n\nBut in this case, the `require('ws')` call in extension.js will fail because `ws` is not available in the extension host. The extension likely crashes on activation because of this.\n\nI need to rewrite the extension without `ws`. I'll use the built-in `http` module instead, which creates an HTTP server that I can use with long polling or Server-Sent Events (SSE). Or even simpler: use `http.createServer()` and have the OpenClaw side use `curl` to POST instructions.\n\nHowever, there's a complication: the extension runs in Cursor's extension host, which is a separate Node.js process started by Electron. The `http` module should be available there.\n\nLet me rewrite the extension using `http` module.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_bT2YWRe1iPc4dCMmiVnQ4590","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * Cursor Bridge Extension\n *\n * Starts an HTTP server and listens for instructions from OpenClaw.\n * When an instruction arrives via POST, it automatically opens the\n * Cursor Agent panel and submits the instruction.\n *\n * Install: Copied to ~/.cursor/extensions/cursor-bridge/\n * Restart Cursor to activate.\n */\n\nconst vscode = require('vscode');\nconst http = require('http');\nconst url = require('url');\n\nlet statusBarItem = null;\nlet server = null;\nlet latestInstruction = '';\nlet logChannel = null;\n\nfunction log(msg) {\n  if (!logChannel) {\n    logChannel = vscode.window.createOutputChannel('Cursor Bridge');\n  }\n  const time = new Date().toLocaleTimeString();\n  logChannel.appendLine(`[${time}] ${msg}`);\n  logChannel.show(true); // show but don't focus\n}\n\n/**\n * Try to send instruction to Cursor Agent using various commands\n */\nasync function sendToAgent(instruction) {\n  log(`Sending instruction: ${instruction.substring(0, 100)}...`);\n\n  try {\n    // Step 1: Try to open/focus the Agent panel\n    const openCommands = [\n      'cursor.composerChatInputFocus',\n      'workspace.action.cursorAgent',\n      'cursorAgent.open',\n      'cursor.chat.openAgentChat',\n      'workbench.action.chat.open',\n    ];\n\n    let opened = false;\n    for (const cmd of openCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        log(`Opened via: ${cmd}`);\n        opened = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (_) {}\n    }\n\n    if (!opened) {\n      log('WARN: Could not open agent panel');\n    }\n\n    await sleep(500);\n\n    // Step 2: Set clipboard text\n    try {\n      await vscode.env.clipboard.writeText(instruction);\n      log('Clipboard set');\n    } catch (e) {\n      log(`Clipboard error: ${e.message}`);\n    }\n\n    await sleep(200);\n\n    // Step 3: Try paste and send\n    let pasted = false;\n    const pasteCommands = [\n      'editor.action.clipboardPasteAction',\n      'cursor.composerChatPaste',\n    ];\n    for (const cmd of pasteCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        log(`Pasted via: ${cmd}`);\n        pasted = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (_) {}\n    }\n\n    await sleep(200);\n\n    // Step 4: Send (Enter)\n    let sent = false;\n    const sendCommands = [\n      'cursor.composerChatSend',\n      'workbench.action.chat.send',\n      'cursorAgent.send',\n    ];\n    for (const cmd of sendCommands) {\n      try {\n        await vscode.commands.executeCommand(cmd);\n        log(`Sent via: ${cmd}`);\n        sent = true;\n        break;\n      } catch (_) {}\n    }\n\n    if (pasted || sent) {\n      log('✅ Instruction delivered');\n      updateStatus('✅');\n      return { success: true, message: 'Instruction sent to agent' };\n    } else {\n      log('⚠️  Partial - instruction is in clipboard, paste manually');\n      updateStatus('📋');\n      return { success: false, message: 'Instruction copied to clipboard. Paste in Cursor Agent (Ctrl+V).' };\n    }\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`Error: ${err.message}`);\n    return { success: false, message: err.message };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction sleep(ms) {\n  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n}\n\nfunction updateStatus(text) {\n  if (statusBarItem) {\n    statusBarItem.text = `$(broadcast) ${text}`;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Start HTTP server\n */\nfunction startServer(port) {\n  try {\n    server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n      // CORS headers\n      res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n      res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n      res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');\n\n      if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n        res.writeHead(204);\n        res.end();\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Parse URL\n      const parsed = url.parse(req.url, true);\n\n      // GET /status\n      if (req.method === 'GET' && (parsed.pathname === '/status' || parsed.pathname === '/')) {\n        res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n        res.end(JSON.stringify({\n          status: 'running',\n          extension: 'cursor-bridge',\n          version: '1.0.0',\n          latestInstruction: latestInstruction || null,\n          port,\n        }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // POST /execute — receive instruction\n      if (req.method === 'POST' && parsed.pathname === '/execute') {\n        let body = '';\n        req.on('data', chunk => body += chunk);\n        req.on('end', async () => {\n          try {\n            const { instruction } = JSON.parse(body);\n            if (!instruction) {\n              res.writeHead(400, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n              res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: 'Missing instruction field' }));\n              return;\n            }\n\n            latestInstruction = instruction;\n            updateStatus('⏳');\n\n            const result = await sendToAgent(instruction);\n\n            res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify(result));\n\n          } catch (err) {\n            log(`Parse error: ${err.message}`);\n            res.writeHead(400, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n            res.end(JSON.stringify({ success: false, error: err.message }));\n          }\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // GET /health\n      if (req.method === 'GET' && parsed.pathname === '/health') {\n        res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n        res.end(JSON.stringify({ status: 'ok', timestamp: Date.now() }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      res.writeHead(404);\n      res.end('Not found');\n    });\n\n    server.listen(port, '127.0.0.1', () => {\n      log(`✅ Ready on http://127.0.0.1:${port}`);\n      updateStatus(`:${port}`);\n    });\n\n    server.on('error', (err) => {\n      log(`Server error: ${err.code || err.message}`);\n      if (err.code === 'EADDRINUSE') {\n        log(`Port ${port} is in use. Try restarting Cursor.`);\n      }\n    });\n\n    return true;\n  } catch (err) {\n    log(`Failed to start: ${err.message}`);\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Extension activate\n */\nfunction activate(context) {\n  log('=== Cursor Bridge activating ===');\n\n  // Status bar\n  statusBarItem = vscode.window.createStatusBarItem(vscode.StatusBarAlignment.Right, 100);\n  statusBarItem.text = '$(broadcast) Starting...';\n  statusBarItem.tooltip = 'Cursor Bridge - OpenClaw integration';\n  statusBarItem.command = 'cursor-bridge.show';\n  statusBarItem.show();\n\n  // Get config port\n  const config = vscode.workspace.getConfiguration('cursorBridge');\n  const port = config.get('port', 18792);\n\n  // Start HTTP server\n  const started = startServer(port);\n  if (!started) {\n    updateStatus('❌');\n    log('Failed to start server');\n  }\n\n  // Register commands\n  const showCommand = vscode.commands.registerCommand('cursor-bridge.show', () => {\n    logChannel.show();\n    vscode.window.showInformationMessage(\n      `Cursor Bridge: ${latestInstruction\n        ? 'Last instruction: ' + latestInstruction.substring(0, 60) + '...'\n        : 'Waiting for instructions...'}`\n    );\n  });\n\n  context.subscriptions.push(statusBarItem, showCommand);\n  log('=== Cursor Bridge activated ===');\n}\n\nfunction deactivate() {\n  if (server) {\n    try { server.close(); } catch (_) {}\n    server = null;\n  }\n  log('Deactivated');\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { activate, deactivate };\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\cursor-bridge\\extension\\extension.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":148,"output":2155,"cacheRead":233984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":236287,"cost":{"input":0.00002072,"output":0.0006034,"cacheRead":0.0065515519999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007175671999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781509062476,"responseId":"317342df-6720-455c-bacc-9486022eb910"}}
