{"type":"message","id":"11f42073","parentId":"d5829eba","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:09.363Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The extension is listed as installed (`openclaw.cursor-bridge` shows up in `--list-extensions`). But the HTTP server isn't listening on port 18792.\n\nLet me check if the extension failed to activate. Let me look for error messages in the extension host logs or check the extension host process.\n\nActually, I just realized something. The extension uses `require('http')` and `require('url')`. These should be available in Node.js. But the issue might be that the extension's `package.json` doesn't have `\"browser\"` or `\"main\"` entry correctly set, or the activation event `onStartupFinished` might not fire properly.\n\nWait, actually I should check if the extension host process is actually running the extension. Let me look at the extension host more carefully.\n\nAnother possibility: Cursor might be using \"Extension isolation\" (from the renderer log: `[CursorExtensionIsolationService] Extension isolation gate is enabled`). This might prevent local extensions from loading.\n\nLet me also check if there's an error in the extension that prevents activation. I can try to look at the extension host output channel in Cursor.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Instead of troubleshooting the extension loading, let me check if the extension is actually activated by looking for the output channel \"Cursor Bridge\" that the extension creates.\n\nLet me also try a simpler approach - maybe I should create the extension as a VS Code Extension Pack or use a different activation event.\n\nActually, the most likely issue is that the `http.createServer` call fails silently, or the extension has a JS error on startup. Since I can't see Console output, let me add more robust error handling and also try to open the output channel programmatically.\n\nBut wait, maybe the problem is simpler. Let me check if the extension host process even has the correct code. The `extension.js` file in the extensions directory might still be the old WebSocket version!\n\nEarlier, I copied the new extension to the extensions directory, but maybe Cursor cached the old version. Let me verify.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SLzFLTAYxXlQGipBEmSz8003","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查扩展目录中的代码是否最新\nSelect-String -Path \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\\extension.js\" -Pattern \"http\\.createServer|require\\('ws'\\)\" | Select-Object -First 5\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Line count ===\"\nGet-Content \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\\extension.js\" | Measure-Object -Line\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Check for common errors ===\"\n# Check package.json\nGet-Content \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\\package.json\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":792,"output":631,"cacheRead":246912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":248335,"cost":{"input":0.00011088000000000001,"output":0.00017668000000000002,"cacheRead":0.006913536,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007201096}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781509380877,"responseId":"e3e23edb-b157-4d67-b847-86ef3a48f8e8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"47ed5c2d","parentId":"11f42073","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:09.644Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_SLzFLTAYxXlQGipBEmSz8003","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\\extension.js:135:    server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\r\n\n=== Line count ===\r\n\r\nLines      : 231\r\nWords      : \r\nCharacters : \r\nProperty   : \r\n\r\n\n=== Check for common errors ===\r\n{\r\n  \"name\": \"cursor-bridge\",\r\n  \"displayName\": \"Cursor Bridge\",\r\n  \"description\": \"Real-time bridge between OpenClaw and Cursor Agent. Receives instructions from OpenClaw via WebSocket and automatically submits them to the Cursor Agent.\",\r\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\r\n  \"publisher\": \"openclaw\",\r\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\r\n  \"engines\": {\r\n    \"vscode\": \"^1.90.0\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"categories\": [\r\n    \"Other\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"activationEvents\": [\r\n    \"onStartupFinished\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"main\": \"./extension.js\",\r\n  \"contributes\": {\r\n    \"commands\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"command\": \"cursor-bridge.show\",\r\n        \"title\": \"OpenClaw: Show Bridge Status\"\r\n      }\r\n    ],\r\n    \"configuration\": {\r\n      \"title\": \"Cursor Bridge\",\r\n      \"properties\": {\r\n        \"cursorBridge.port\": {\r\n          \"type\": \"number\",\r\n          \"default\": 18792,\r\n          \"description\": \"WebSocket server port for receiving instructions from OpenClaw\"\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":264,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\\extension.js:135:    server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\r\n\n=== Line count ===\r\n\r\nLines      : 231\r\nWords      : \r\nCharacters : \r\nProperty   : \r\n\r\n\n=== Check for common errors ===\r\n{\r\n  \"name\": \"cursor-bridge\",\r\n  \"displayName\": \"Cursor Bridge\",\r\n  \"description\": \"Real-time bridge between OpenClaw and Cursor Agent. Receives instructions from OpenClaw via WebSocket and automatically submits them to the Cursor Agent.\",\r\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\r\n  \"publisher\": \"openclaw\",\r\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\r\n  \"engines\": {\r\n    \"vscode\": \"^1.90.0\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"categories\": [\r\n    \"Other\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"activationEvents\": [\r\n    \"onStartupFinished\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"main\": \"./extension.js\",\r\n  \"contributes\": {\r\n    \"commands\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"command\": \"cursor-bridge.show\",\r\n        \"title\": \"OpenClaw: Show Bridge Status\"\r\n      }\r\n    ],\r\n    \"configuration\": {\r\n      \"title\": \"Cursor Bridge\",\r\n      \"properties\": {\r\n        \"cursorBridge.port\": {\r\n          \"type\": \"number\",\r\n          \"default\": 18792,\r\n          \"description\": \"WebSocket server port for receiving instructions from OpenClaw\"\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781509389644}}
{"type":"message","id":"f217c784","parentId":"47ed5c2d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:16.716Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The extension files look correct - it uses `http.createServer` (not WebSocket), and the package.json is properly formatted.\n\nBut there's a potential issue: the `http.createServer` needs the `http` module, which should be available in the extension host running in Node.js. But the extension host might be running in a sandboxed environment.\n\nLet me check the extension host process details to see if there are errors.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Let me check if there's a way to debug the extension by looking at the output channel programmatically. Or, let me just modify the extension to log to a file instead of the console, so I can see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_spykpKMV4fV6xlMFBCpY2810","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check extension host process for errors\n# First, find the extension host process\n$extHostPid = 14144  # from the log\n\n# Check exit codes and errors\n$logs20260615T154140 = \"20260615T154140\"\nSelect-String -Path \"$env:APPDATA\\Cursor\\logs\\$logs20260615T154140\\main.log\" -Pattern \"extension\" -Context 0,3 | Select-Object -First 15\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Check if extension host is alive ===\"\n$proc = Get-Process -Id 14144 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nif ($proc) {\n    Write-Output \"Extension host PID 14144 is alive\"\n} else {\n    Write-Output \"Extension host PID 14144 is DEAD\"\n}\n\n# Try another approach: check all extension host processes\n$extHosts = Get-Process -Name \"Cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Where-Object { $_.StartTime -gt (Get-Date).AddMinutes(-2) }\nWrite-Output \"Recent Cursor processes:\"\n$extHosts | Select-Object Id, StartTime | Format-Table\n\n# Check if there's an extension host error by looking at the renderer more carefully\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Fu