{"type":"message","id":"5ed91267","parentId":"9ea49eab","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:36.868Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, I see something important in the `trustedExtensionPublishers`:\n```json\n\"trustedExtensionPublishers\": [\"microsoft\",\"github\",\"anysphere\",\"ms-toolsai\",\"ms-python\",\"ms-dotnettools\",\"ms-azuretools\",\"ms-vscode\",\"ms-vsliveshare\"]\n```\n\nMy extension's publisher is `openclaw` which is NOT in the trusted publishers list. This might cause Cursor to silently skip loading it.\n\nBut more importantly, Cursor might simply not load local extensions that aren't installed through its marketplace. The `anysphere.remote-ssh` extension is installed through the gallery, while `openclaw.cursor-bridge` is installed manually from a local folder.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of trying to hack Cursor's extension loading, let me:\n\n1. Create the extension properly using `cursor --install-extension` or similar\n2. Or package it as a VSIX and install it\n\nActually, Cursor might not have a `--install-extension` from local path (it's a Cursor-specific thing). But `cursor --install-extension` should exist as part of the VS Code CLI API.\n\nLet me try installing the extension via the CLI.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_oKYI4Ds1tbrGUlOl6nke3616","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 尝试通过 CLI 安装扩展\n# 先打包成 vsix (实际上可以直接指定目录)\ncursor --install-extension \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\" 2>&1\n\n# 或者看看是否需要完整路径\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Alternative: try --install-extension with publisher.name ===\"\ncursor --install-extension openclaw.cursor-bridge 2>&1\n\n# 或者检查是否可以通过 VSIX 安装\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Check vsce existence ===\"\nGet-Command vsce -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Source","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":11508,"output":457,"cacheRead":250496,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":262461,"cost":{"input":0.0016111200000000002,"output":0.00012796000000000001,"cacheRead":0.007013888,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.008752968}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781509408650,"responseId":"3e536880-76f9-486b-b250-109ee45fdc2f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"da97a5fd","parentId":"5ed91267","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:38.207Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_oKYI4Ds1tbrGUlOl6nke3616","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Installing extensions...\ncursor : (node:23212) [DEP0040] DeprecationWarning: The `punycode` module is deprecated. Please use a userland alternat\r\nive instead.\r\n所在位置 行:3 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --install-extension \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\curso ...\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: ((node:23212) [D...native instead.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n(Use `Cursor --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\r\nExtension 'c:\\users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge' not found.\r\nMake sure you use the full extension ID, including the publisher, e.g.: anysphere.csharp\r\nFailed Installing Extensions: c:\\users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\r\n\n=== Alternative: try --install-extension with publisher.name ===\r\ncursor : (node:11068) [DEP0040] DeprecationWarning: The `punycode` module is deprecated. Please use a userland alternat\r\nive instead.\r\n所在位置 行:7 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --install-extension openclaw.cursor-bridge 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: ((node:11068) [D...native instead.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n(Use `Cursor --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\r\nInstalling extensions...\nExtension 'openclaw.cursor-bridge' v1.0.0 is already installed. Use '--force' option to update to latest version or provide '@<version>' to install a specific version, for example: 'openclaw.cursor-bridge@1.2.3'.\n\n=== Check vsce existence ===\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":1323,"aggregated":"Installing extensions...\ncursor : (node:23212) [DEP0040] DeprecationWarning: The `punycode` module is deprecated. Please use a userland alternat\r\nive instead.\r\n所在位置 行:3 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --install-extension \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.cursor\\extensions\\curso ...\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: ((node:23212) [D...native instead.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n(Use `Cursor --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\r\nExtension 'c:\\users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge' not found.\r\nMake sure you use the full extension ID, including the publisher, e.g.: anysphere.csharp\r\nFailed Installing Extensions: c:\\users\\yyzypublic\\.cursor\\extensions\\cursor-bridge\r\n\n=== Alternative: try --install-extension with publisher.name ===\r\ncursor : (node:11068) [DEP0040] DeprecationWarning: The `punycode` module is deprecated. Please use a userland alternat\r\nive instead.\r\n所在位置 行:7 字符: 1\r\n+ cursor --install-extension openclaw.cursor-bridge 2>&1\r\n+ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: ((node:11068) [D...native instead.:String) [], RemoteException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NativeCommandError\r\n \r\n(Use `Cursor --trace-deprecation ...` to show where the warning was created)\r\nInstalling extensions...\nExtension 'openclaw.cursor-bridge' v1.0.0 is already installed. Use '--force' option to update to latest version or provide '@<version>' to install a specific version, for example: 'openclaw.cursor-bridge@1.2.3'.\n\n=== Check vsce existence ===\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781509418207}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3b9a9b9","parentId":"da97a5fd","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:46.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The extension IS installed:\n- `cursor --install-extension openclaw.cursor-bridge` says it's \"already installed\"\n- But `cursor --install-extension \"path\"` says \"not found\" (it's looking for the full path as an extension ID)\n\nSo the extension IS installed but just not activating. Let me check if the extension host has any errors by looking at the extension's output channel.\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is that `require('http')` doesn't work in the extension host when running in \"browser\" mode. Some VS Code extension hosts run in a sandboxed environment where `http` is not available.\n\nBut that's usually only for web extensions. Local extensions should have full Node.js API access.\n\nLet me check if there's an error in the extension host by looking at the Cursor logs more carefully. Or better yet, let me modify the extension to write to a file for debugging.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Let me not use the VS Code extensions API at all. Instead, let me try to directly call Cursor's API through the VS Code IPC pipe.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_NC3ayU6x25hQd5JyWT7L8501","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to directly connect to the VS Code IPC socket\n# VS Code uses named pipes for inter-process communication\n# Format: \\\\.\\pipe\\vscode-ipc-<guid>-sock\n\n# List available IPC pipes\n$pipes = [System.IO.Directory]::GetFiles(\"\\\\.\\\\pipe\\\\\") | Where-Object { $_ -match \"vscode\" }\nWrite-Output \"Available IPC pipes:\"\n$pipes | ForEach-Object { Write-Output \"  $_\" }\n\nif ($pipes.Count -gt 0) {\n    $pipe = $pipes[0]\n    Write-Output \"`nTrying to connect to: $pipe\"\n    \n    # Try to connect and send a command\n    $client = New-Object System.IO.Pipes.NamedPipeClientStream(\".\", ($pipe -replace \"\\\\\\\\\\\\.\\\\\\\\pipe\\\\\\\\\", \"\"), [System.IO.Pipes.PipeDirection]::InOut)\n    try {\n        $client.Connect(2000)\n        Write-Output \"Connected to pipe!\"\n        \n        $writer = New-Object System.IO.StreamWriter($client)\n        $reader = New-Object System.IO.StreamReader($client)\n        \n        # Send a simple message\n        $writer.WriteLine('{\"type\":\"ping\"}')\n        $writer.Flush()\n        Start-Sleep -Milliseconds 500\n        \n        if ($client.IsConnected) {\n            $response = $reader.ReadLine()\n            Write-Output \"Response: $response\"\n        }\n        $client.Close()\n    } catch {\n        Write-Output \"Connection failed: $_\"\n    }\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":544,"output":636,"cacheRead":262400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":263580,"cost":{"input":0.00007616,"output":0.00017808,"cacheRead":0.0073472,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00760144}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781509418212,"responseId":"9e87f48e-ad12-4975-87f3-253fe866375a"}}
