{"type":"message","id":"3b4f23da","parentId":"8d65d8a6","timestamp":"2026-06-15T07:43:58.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The named pipe connection timed out. This is because the IPC pipe is used by Cursor's own processes and might not accept external connections, or it uses a specific protocol that requires proper authentication/handshake.\n\nLet me try yet another approach. I'll write a different kind of extension that doesn't need `http` module but uses a simpler mechanism. Or better yet, let me check if the extension host can load the extension by looking at WHY it's not activating.\n\nActually, let me re-read the renderer.log more carefully. I see \"Started local extension host with pid 18712\" from the old session. Let me check if the extension host was started in the NEW session.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6jFSZAAq7rU3gnsGSByW4070","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if extension host was started in the new session\nGet-Content \"$env:APPDATA\\Cursor\\logs\\20260615T154140\\window1_wb0\\renderer.log\" | Select-String \"extension host|extensionHost|started\" -Context 0,2\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Check extension host process ===\"\n$cursorProcs = Get-Process -Name \"Cursor\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Sort-Object StartTime\n$cursorProcs | Select-Object Id, StartTime, @{N='CmdLine';E={$_.CommandLine -replace '.{100}','...'}} | Format-Table\n\nWrite-Output \"`n=== Check if extension host has command line with extensions ===\"\nGet-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter \"name = 'Cursor.exe'\" | Select-Object ProcessId, CommandLine | \n    Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match \"extension\" } | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":191,"output":414,"cacheRead":263552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":264157,"cost":{"input":0.00002674,"output":0.00011592,"cacheRead":0.00737945